1
00:00:26,051 --> 00:00:29,054
SIX SINGLES UNDER ONE ROOF

2
00:00:29,121 --> 00:00:30,422
DAY 4, DINNER

3
00:00:30,489 --> 00:00:33,659
THEY'RE ON THE SAME WAVELENGTH NOW

4
00:00:33,726 --> 00:00:35,461
Look forward to dinner this evening.

5
00:00:35,527 --> 00:00:36,729
What are you making?

6
00:00:36,795 --> 00:00:38,330
Pork cutlet.
We're having a fancy meal.

7
00:00:38,397 --> 00:00:39,732
- For real?
- Sure.

8
00:00:39,798 --> 00:00:41,033
Everyone loves cream soup.

9
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:43,769
- Why don't we make it?
- It'd be great.

10
00:00:43,836 --> 00:00:44,837
All right.

11
00:00:44,903 --> 00:00:47,606
AT THAT MOMENT
SOO-JIN COMES OUT OF HER ROOM

12
00:00:48,140 --> 00:00:50,075
Are the three of you
preparing dinner today?

13
00:00:50,142 --> 00:00:51,276
- Sorry?
- Are you guys cooking?

14
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:53,012
Yes, we're running the show today.

15
00:00:53,946 --> 00:00:56,715
DO YOUR OWN THING...

16
00:00:57,683 --> 00:01:00,786
THINGS HAVE GOTTEN
EXTREMELY CHILL HERE

17
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:04,423
- Should we split up the tasks?
- I guess we can do that.

18
00:01:04,490 --> 00:01:05,924
Do you want to handle deep-frying

19
00:01:05,991 --> 00:01:07,726
or prepare the cabbage
and make the cream soup?

20
00:01:07,793 --> 00:01:08,794
The latter.

21
00:01:08,861 --> 00:01:09,928
I'll do the deep-frying, then.

22
00:01:10,996 --> 00:01:13,098
I'll help wherever needed.

23
00:01:13,165 --> 00:01:14,166
Great.

24
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:17,136
I'd feel more at ease
if you did the main dish.

25
00:01:17,436 --> 00:01:19,204
No, I'd rather not act up so much.

26
00:01:19,271 --> 00:01:20,606
Always keep your head down.

27
00:01:21,473 --> 00:01:22,474
NO MORE ACTING UP
MAIN CHEF JANG KEUN-SUK

28
00:01:22,541 --> 00:01:24,376
The cabbage needs
to be sliced paper-thin, Daniel.

29
00:01:24,576 --> 00:01:26,078
I'll slice up the cabbage first.

30
00:01:26,679 --> 00:01:27,746
You know me.

31
00:01:27,813 --> 00:01:29,448
I'm the dumb type
to hurt myself right away.

32
00:01:29,515 --> 00:01:31,750
TROUBLEMAKER IN THE KITCHEN
SOUS-CHEF DANIEL

33
00:01:32,818 --> 00:01:34,186
No, you're not.

34
00:01:34,453 --> 00:01:36,055
You're a novice, that's all.

35
00:01:36,689 --> 00:01:39,425
ANGEL ON DISH DUTY
ASSISTANT AHN JAE-HYEON

36
00:01:39,491 --> 00:01:40,826
I never imagined deep-frying at home.

37
00:01:40,893 --> 00:01:42,394
Just roughly chop it. Oh, no.

38
00:01:42,461 --> 00:01:45,364
WITH NO ONE TO HOLD THEM BACK...
WILL THEY MANAGE OKAY?

39
00:01:46,198 --> 00:01:47,533
I'll help out, too.

40
00:01:47,599 --> 00:01:49,368
You want to have a go at slicing?

41
00:01:49,435 --> 00:01:52,104
Chop this into four equal parts,
then slice everything.

42
00:01:52,171 --> 00:01:53,372
THE SOUS-CHEF SEEMS GIDDY

43
00:01:53,639 --> 00:01:55,908
Give me a demonstration.

44
00:01:55,974 --> 00:01:56,975
IT'S THEIR OWN LITTLE WORLD

45
00:01:57,042 --> 00:01:58,110
A demonstration?

46
00:01:58,510 --> 00:01:59,878
- A demonstration?
- I'll do exactly the same.

47
00:01:59,945 --> 00:02:01,013
Here's what I think.

48
00:02:01,647 --> 00:02:02,648
Just roughly chop it.

49
00:02:02,715 --> 00:02:04,116
Oh, no. I got it wrong.

50
00:02:04,349 --> 00:02:06,185
- Don't forget to remove the core.
- Okay.

51
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:09,488
Removing the core isn't a big deal.

52
00:02:09,555 --> 00:02:10,622
- Okay.
- We don't need this.

53
00:02:11,490 --> 00:02:12,691
NOT A BIG DEAL?

54
00:02:12,758 --> 00:02:13,759
- We can remove this much.
- Okay.

55
00:02:13,826 --> 00:02:14,827
NO, I'LL KEEP MY HEAD DOWN

56
00:02:14,893 --> 00:02:16,061
IGNORING AS BEST AS HE CAN

57
00:02:16,128 --> 00:02:18,731
- Next, I slice it into thin strips?
- Yeah.

58
00:02:19,765 --> 00:02:21,500
- As thin as I can, right?
- Yes.

59
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:22,701
THIS IS IT, RIGHT?

60
00:02:24,002 --> 00:02:25,771
SLIPS

61
00:02:25,838 --> 00:02:27,573
TAKES A GLANCE

62
00:02:27,639 --> 00:02:29,374
HAWK-EYED

63
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:30,876
HE'D RATHER SIT THIS OUT

64
00:02:30,943 --> 00:02:33,378
BUT THINGS KEEP BUGGING HIM

65
00:02:33,445 --> 00:02:36,281
PACING

66
00:02:36,348 --> 00:02:38,684
ANXIOUS

67
00:02:38,751 --> 00:02:41,286
MEDDLING 1
USE THIS...

68
00:02:41,687 --> 00:02:42,788
Here's a peeler.

69
00:02:42,855 --> 00:02:44,456
Oh, okay.

70
00:02:44,523 --> 00:02:45,924
MEDDLING 2
USE THIS AS WELL...

71
00:02:46,525 --> 00:02:49,128
I'LL JUST ACT UP AND MEDDLE

72
00:02:49,595 --> 00:02:51,396
ALL SET!

73
00:02:51,463 --> 00:02:53,565
I'll show you
my double-wok technique today.

74
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:56,101
WITNESS AP'S SKILL

75
00:02:56,735 --> 00:03:00,606
AP'S PORK CUTLETS AREN'T ORDINARY

76
00:03:00,939 --> 00:03:02,207
I love the sizzling sound.

77
00:03:02,808 --> 00:03:03,909
Like a gentle rain, right?

78
00:03:03,976 --> 00:03:05,110
FRYING CUTLETS IN BOTH WOKS

79
00:03:05,410 --> 00:03:08,347
We will fry the pork cutlets twice.

80
00:03:08,881 --> 00:03:10,983
It makes it all crispy and nice.

81
00:03:11,049 --> 00:03:14,453
AP ALWAYS GOES THE EXTRA MILE,
EVEN WITH READY-MADE MEALS

82
00:03:14,753 --> 00:03:17,156
Back in the day,
butchers sold pork cutlet cuts.

83
00:03:17,222 --> 00:03:19,591
- Yes, they did.
- They don't these days.

84
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:21,126
Pork cutlets are less work these days

85
00:03:21,193 --> 00:03:23,195
- thanks to ready-made products.
- I suppose so.

86
00:03:23,262 --> 00:03:25,164
We had to hammer the meat
back in the day.

87
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:27,399
EVERYTHING IS SO MUCH EASIER NOW

88
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,301
Guys, here's an idea.

89
00:03:29,368 --> 00:03:32,404
I noticed how warm the weather was
while hanging our laundry to dry.

90
00:03:32,471 --> 00:03:33,539
Yeah, it's noticeably warmer.

91
00:03:33,605 --> 00:03:37,042
What do you say to having dinner
out on the second-floor terrace?

92
00:03:37,109 --> 00:03:38,944
- What do you think?
- I love the idea.

93
00:03:39,011 --> 00:03:40,012
Upstairs?

94
00:03:40,379 --> 00:03:43,782
INTRODUCING THE 2ND-FLOOR TERRACE
BESIDE THE GUYS' ROOMS

95
00:03:45,450 --> 00:03:47,986
DURING THE DAY
YOU CAN SOAK IN THE SUN

96
00:03:48,053 --> 00:03:52,624
DURING THE NIGHT
YOU CAN SOAK UP THE ROMANTIC VIBE

97
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:55,093
- We haven't been there together.
- No.

98
00:03:55,294 --> 00:03:57,729
Do-yeon and the others
haven't come upstairs, right?

99
00:03:57,796 --> 00:03:59,164
- Not together, no.
- Right.

100
00:04:00,465 --> 00:04:04,703
LET'S RECREATE THE DISH
FROM OUR CHILDHOOD!

101
00:04:05,237 --> 00:04:08,473
COOL THE PORK CUTLETS
AFTER FRYING THEM FOR THE 1ST TIME

102
00:04:08,907 --> 00:04:10,409
Now comes the second round.

103
00:04:11,043 --> 00:04:12,878
Here we go.

104
00:04:12,945 --> 00:04:14,213
FRYING THE SECOND TIME

105
00:04:14,279 --> 00:04:18,250
TO GIVE THE CUTLETS
THE GLORIOUS GOLDEN-BROWN CRUST

106
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,919
I'm losing my mind here.
These look so delicious.

107
00:04:22,020 --> 00:04:23,222
They smell amazing, too.

108
00:04:23,288 --> 00:04:24,590
THE NOSTALGIC AROMA FILLS THE KITCHEN

109
00:04:26,091 --> 00:04:27,226
TIME TO PLATE THE OLD-SCHOOL WAY

110
00:04:27,292 --> 00:04:28,393
Like this, you know.

111
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:29,561
I love it.

112
00:04:30,596 --> 00:04:31,830
JAE-HYEON IN THE MEANTIME...

113
00:04:31,897 --> 00:04:33,432
You never know how it will turn out.

114
00:04:33,498 --> 00:04:34,900
Roll them into rice balls?

115
00:04:34,967 --> 00:04:37,536
A ROUND BALL OF RICE IS THE SIGNATURE
OF A KOREAN-EUROPEAN FUSION MEAL

116
00:04:38,203 --> 00:04:39,872
HOW DO I MAKE THAT, THOUGH?

117
00:04:40,439 --> 00:04:42,274
JUST A SECOND

118
00:04:42,841 --> 00:04:45,644
WHY IS DANIEL WASHING HIS HANDS?

119
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:48,680
Like this? Wait, it's hot.

120
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:49,748
Let me at it.

121
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:54,219
SHAPING A BALL

122
00:04:54,553 --> 00:04:57,489
MR. NATURAL CHOOSES
THE MOST RUDIMENTARY WAY POSSIBLE

123
00:04:57,556 --> 00:04:59,024
- Adding your magic touch?
- You bet.

124
00:05:00,492 --> 00:05:01,727
It's piping hot.

125
00:05:01,793 --> 00:05:04,496
ADDING THE MAGIC TOUCH THE OLD WAY
RATHER THAN USING A TOOL

126
00:05:07,399 --> 00:05:08,700
BYE-BYE, PRINTS
WELCOME, OLD MEMORIES

127
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,168
It's so hot. What should I do?

128
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:12,571
I'm the king of sushi.

129
00:05:13,572 --> 00:05:14,606
They all look so neat.

130
00:05:14,673 --> 00:05:16,275
- Right?
- They look great.

131
00:05:18,076 --> 00:05:21,947
THESE CHILIS TASTE BEST
WHEN YOU HAVE THEM WHOLE

132
00:05:22,014 --> 00:05:23,749
- Pickled radish.
- Three pieces each.

133
00:05:23,815 --> 00:05:25,017
Three each.

134
00:05:25,284 --> 00:05:27,619
It's as if we're preparing
a school meal.

135
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:31,323
A PLAIN BUT HEARTY MEAL
IN A CLASSIC OLD-FASHIONED WAY

136
00:05:31,556 --> 00:05:32,591
I'll take the sauce.

137
00:05:32,658 --> 00:05:34,126
- Give it the classic look.
- Okay.

138
00:05:34,526 --> 00:05:35,527
Here we go.

139
00:05:35,594 --> 00:05:36,628
SPILLING ALL OVER

140
00:05:36,695 --> 00:05:38,430
- Come on.
- No way.

141
00:05:38,931 --> 00:05:40,399
A CRUDE SPLASH OF SAUCE
ON THE PERFECT MEAL

142
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:41,600
Did you hear our sighs?

143
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:42,968
It was perfect...

144
00:05:43,268 --> 00:05:44,436
Give it a go, then.

145
00:05:44,503 --> 00:05:45,737
TOSSING THE BOTTLE TO JAE-HYEON

146
00:05:45,804 --> 00:05:46,805
Over here.

147
00:05:48,307 --> 00:05:49,374
Shoot, this is difficult.

148
00:05:49,441 --> 00:05:50,842
JAE-HYEON FAILS, TOO

149
00:05:52,978 --> 00:05:54,012
- This...
- Here, Keun-suk.

150
00:05:54,613 --> 00:05:55,881
Show us how it's done, Keun-chan.

151
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:57,416
Try this one.

152
00:05:58,150 --> 00:06:00,319
LET ME TAKE A LUMP OUT FIRST!

153
00:06:00,519 --> 00:06:02,854
One, two, three.

154
00:06:06,858 --> 00:06:08,260
EXCLAIMING IN UNISON

155
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:10,095
DEEPLY MOVED

156
00:06:10,429 --> 00:06:12,664
I'M AP, REMEMBER?

157
00:06:12,731 --> 00:06:13,732
It looks so pretty.

158
00:06:13,799 --> 00:06:14,800
Neat, right?

159
00:06:14,866 --> 00:06:16,034
WOULD YOU LOOK AT THAT?

160
00:06:16,101 --> 00:06:17,903
That was very nice.

161
00:06:17,970 --> 00:06:19,404
I'll add the sauce now.

162
00:06:19,471 --> 00:06:20,572
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

163
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,675
THE SAUCE SHOULD BE POURED
FOR A KOREAN-EUROPEAN FUSION MEAL

164
00:06:23,742 --> 00:06:25,744
- It looks amazing.
- It's great.

165
00:06:25,811 --> 00:06:27,412
What's the sauce called again?

166
00:06:27,479 --> 00:06:28,580
Urethane?

167
00:06:28,647 --> 00:06:29,815
- Worcestershire.
- Worcestershire?

168
00:06:29,881 --> 00:06:31,650
Urethane would kill you.

169
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:33,819
AP'S WORCESTERSHIRE SAUCE
AS A FINISHING TOUCH

170
00:06:33,885 --> 00:06:35,220
- Great.
- All right.

171
00:06:35,287 --> 00:06:36,488
All right!

172
00:06:36,555 --> 00:06:38,557
- Let's go.
- It's perfect.

173
00:06:39,091 --> 00:06:40,892
It's time for dinner!

174
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:42,094
Let's move.

175
00:06:43,161 --> 00:06:44,162
You're done already?

176
00:06:44,229 --> 00:06:45,664
- Let's go.
- Of course.

177
00:06:45,731 --> 00:06:47,432
- Really?
- We have to bring a plate up each.

178
00:06:47,632 --> 00:06:49,101
- Let's go.
- Bring a plate...

179
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:50,802
YOU CAN'T HELP BUT EXCLAIM
AT THE GLORIOUS SIGHT

180
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:53,338
APPLAUSE

181
00:06:54,906 --> 00:06:56,508
- Don't they look so lovely?
- Wow, guys.

182
00:06:56,575 --> 00:06:58,677
GUYS IN OUR FAM ARE ON THE BALL!

183
00:06:58,744 --> 00:07:00,212
This is amazing.

184
00:07:00,278 --> 00:07:01,546
Look at all this, Da-hee.

185
00:07:02,381 --> 00:07:04,883
IN A GREAT MOOD

186
00:07:05,784 --> 00:07:06,985
- What's all this?
- All right.

187
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:08,153
First off...

188
00:07:09,187 --> 00:07:10,689
I'm starving.

189
00:07:10,889 --> 00:07:12,124
You've outdone yourselves, guys.

190
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:13,759
I like pork cutlets.

191
00:07:14,493 --> 00:07:15,827
Hey, this is great!

192
00:07:16,194 --> 00:07:17,362
So romantic!

193
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:21,166
<i>Would you believe it?</i>

194
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:23,168
<i>It's so beautiful here.</i>

195
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:25,203
UNDERNEATH THE GLAMOROUS LIGHTS

196
00:07:25,804 --> 00:07:27,239
<i>It looks so good.</i>

197
00:07:27,305 --> 00:07:29,875
I don't know what to do
with the feast we've got here.

198
00:07:29,941 --> 00:07:31,143
Tell me if you need extra plates.

199
00:07:31,209 --> 00:07:33,078
- Let's clink our glasses.
- Thank you for the meal.

200
00:07:33,145 --> 00:07:36,081
- Good work today.
- Great job, everyone.

201
00:07:36,948 --> 00:07:41,019
A SWIG OF ICE-COLD BEER
TO EASE THE BURDEN OF THE DAY

202
00:07:41,086 --> 00:07:42,788
REFRESHING

203
00:07:44,256 --> 00:07:45,891
THAT HITS THE SPOT

204
00:07:47,526 --> 00:07:49,027
SODA

205
00:07:49,094 --> 00:07:50,228
Why is this so good?

206
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:53,932
Looks like you're enjoying a beer.

207
00:07:53,999 --> 00:07:55,000
SODA GOT ME DRUNK

208
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:57,669
- It's going down so smoothly.
- Bon appétit.

209
00:07:57,736 --> 00:08:00,272
- Bon appétit.
- Bon appétit.

210
00:08:00,806 --> 00:08:02,407
Oh, wow.

211
00:08:02,474 --> 00:08:05,410
You all seem extra excited today.

212
00:08:05,477 --> 00:08:08,013
- It's so tender.
- All prepared with so much care.

213
00:08:10,515 --> 00:08:12,084
- It's giving restaurant food.
- Totally.

214
00:08:12,150 --> 00:08:13,952
- It brings me back.
- Really?

215
00:08:14,019 --> 00:08:16,088
- Really? Have you tried it already?
- It's really old-school.

216
00:08:17,522 --> 00:08:18,657
RIGHT FROM THEIR CHILDHOOD!

217
00:08:18,723 --> 00:08:20,492
- You get it, right?
- It's just right.

218
00:08:22,227 --> 00:08:23,462
This is insane.

219
00:08:23,528 --> 00:08:26,298
THE TASTE BRINGS
ALL THE MEMORIES BACK

220
00:08:26,498 --> 00:08:28,567
- It's so good.
- The sauce is incredible, too.

221
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,268
- The sauce is good, right?
- It's so crispy.

222
00:08:30,335 --> 00:08:31,503
I fried them twice.

223
00:08:32,237 --> 00:08:33,472
It's amazing.

224
00:08:33,705 --> 00:08:35,240
- It's amazing.
- You fried them twice?

225
00:08:37,342 --> 00:08:38,343
ENTHRALLED

226
00:08:38,410 --> 00:08:40,245
- You did a great job.
- It's freaking incredible.

227
00:08:40,312 --> 00:08:41,613
- It's so good.
- Happy to hear that.

228
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:43,615
- It's amazing.
- Totally.

229
00:08:44,616 --> 00:08:46,184
- I love the vibe here, too.
- Same.

230
00:08:46,585 --> 00:08:49,254
It's different from downstairs,
but it has its own charm.

231
00:08:49,321 --> 00:08:50,322
A DIFFERENT CHARM

232
00:08:50,722 --> 00:08:53,191
I think I'll miss this house badly.

233
00:08:53,258 --> 00:08:55,327
- Really? You feel that way already?
- Yeah.

234
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,796
- I get attached easily.
- Okay.

235
00:08:57,863 --> 00:08:59,498
- I can see that.
- I'm affectionate deep inside.

236
00:08:59,564 --> 00:09:00,632
- Really?
- Sure.

237
00:09:00,699 --> 00:09:02,434
- I'm surprised.
- I'm caring on the inside.

238
00:09:02,801 --> 00:09:06,104
I don't think I could feel this way
with another group of people.

239
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:07,973
What's with you?
It feels like this is our last day.

240
00:09:08,039 --> 00:09:09,374
Oh, well...

241
00:09:09,441 --> 00:09:11,810
I want to make
as many memories as I can

242
00:09:11,877 --> 00:09:12,911
so I won't regret it later.

243
00:09:13,578 --> 00:09:14,913
That thought hit me suddenly.

244
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:17,182
Let's give each other lots of love
while we have the time.

245
00:09:17,415 --> 00:09:18,650
Here's to giving lots of love.

246
00:09:18,717 --> 00:09:20,519
- Lots of love.
- We only have days left now.

247
00:09:20,585 --> 00:09:23,722
- Cheers.
- Actually, I've had this thought.

248
00:09:25,790 --> 00:09:28,860
I want to go all-in
and be really close with you guys.

249
00:09:28,927 --> 00:09:30,395
Even if we never meet again

250
00:09:30,462 --> 00:09:32,597
- I still want us to get close.
- So soon?

251
00:09:32,797 --> 00:09:33,932
So soon?

252
00:09:33,999 --> 00:09:35,534
You're already considering
cutting us off?

253
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,969
- Why would you say that?
- "We're going our separate ways

254
00:09:38,036 --> 00:09:40,138
but let's pretend to be close
until the end."

255
00:09:40,772 --> 00:09:42,674
You and your stupid filterless mouth!

256
00:09:42,741 --> 00:09:45,310
ANOTHER UNFILTERED INTRUSIVE THOUGHT

257
00:09:45,577 --> 00:09:49,181
- Tomorrow night is the halfway mark.
- You're right.

258
00:09:49,414 --> 00:09:51,616
Can you believe it?
Our days together are numbered.

259
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:53,318
WHAT A DRAMATIC WAY TO PUT IT

260
00:09:53,385 --> 00:09:54,486
You startled me.

261
00:09:54,553 --> 00:09:56,555
That seriously rattled me, too.

262
00:09:56,621 --> 00:09:58,156
I mean, our shoot is set to end.

263
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:00,025
- Do we only have six more days?
- It's going to end.

264
00:10:00,091 --> 00:10:04,462
ONE PERSON HAS GROWN
NOTICEABLY SILENT

265
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:06,765
WE MIGHT NOT SEE AGAIN?

266
00:10:06,831 --> 00:10:09,367
OUR DAYS TOGETHER ARE NUMBERED?

267
00:10:10,502 --> 00:10:11,503
SO MELANCHOLY...

268
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:13,371
Just a scene from a TV show
hits me like a truck

269
00:10:13,438 --> 00:10:14,439
because I relate to it.

270
00:10:14,506 --> 00:10:16,841
THESE THOUGHTS
ARE DESTROYING HER APPETITE

271
00:10:16,908 --> 00:10:19,244
I don't like that about myself,
but I get so sad that way.

272
00:10:19,311 --> 00:10:20,312
DOWNCAST

273
00:10:20,378 --> 00:10:23,148
I've tried to bear it,
but just the thought alone...

274
00:10:23,215 --> 00:10:24,349
STARES

275
00:10:24,683 --> 00:10:26,451
You're not crying, are you?

276
00:10:26,518 --> 00:10:28,186
- You're not crying, are you?
- What?

277
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:30,689
I swear she's getting ready to cry.

278
00:10:30,922 --> 00:10:33,525
- No, she's savoring the cutlet.
- Yeah.

279
00:10:33,592 --> 00:10:34,793
She was getting all teary.

280
00:10:34,859 --> 00:10:36,528
- That's not it.
- She's savoring the cutlet.

281
00:10:37,362 --> 00:10:39,464
Let's share our tear-up triggers.

282
00:10:40,532 --> 00:10:41,766
Actually

283
00:10:42,234 --> 00:10:44,736
something personal doesn't move me.

284
00:10:45,537 --> 00:10:46,671
So you need to think about others?

285
00:10:46,738 --> 00:10:48,907
Yeah, I guess.
I'm sure you guys feel the same.

286
00:10:49,908 --> 00:10:52,143
If someone acts like they're fine
when they're obviously not

287
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:53,211
it really...

288
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:54,846
What was that?

289
00:10:54,913 --> 00:10:56,548
Guys, look.

290
00:10:56,615 --> 00:10:57,616
ALMOST TEARED UP

291
00:10:57,682 --> 00:10:59,417
Did you see that?
If the lamps had come a bit lower

292
00:10:59,484 --> 00:11:01,052
they would've hit my neck!

293
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:02,187
Look at them.

294
00:11:02,254 --> 00:11:04,089
- Just look.
- Like in <i>Final Destination </i>series.

295
00:11:04,155 --> 00:11:05,423
I love that franchise.

296
00:11:05,490 --> 00:11:06,591
DO-YEON CAN ALWAYS MAKE HIM SMILE

297
00:11:06,658 --> 00:11:08,426
- Guys, I'm terrified.
- Seriously, Do-yeon...

298
00:11:08,493 --> 00:11:11,229
- That would've been hilarious.
- I was obviously the target.

299
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:13,698
That looks about right.

300
00:11:14,299 --> 00:11:15,967
It might end up falling again.

301
00:11:16,034 --> 00:11:17,168
- Should I remove them?
- Hold them up.

302
00:11:17,235 --> 00:11:19,604
- I'll remove them.
- Are they too high up for you?

303
00:11:19,671 --> 00:11:21,072
- Should I handle them?
- Da-hee...

304
00:11:21,773 --> 00:11:23,308
Wait, isn't he taller than you?

305
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:24,442
Isn't Jae-hyeon taller?

306
00:11:24,509 --> 00:11:26,177
It's nice to have
so many tall people around.

307
00:11:26,244 --> 00:11:28,246
- Lucky you, tall folks.
- I kind of fixed them.

308
00:11:28,713 --> 00:11:31,216
HIS GAZE FIXES ON SOMETHING

309
00:11:31,283 --> 00:11:33,018
Are you in your long johns or what?

310
00:11:33,084 --> 00:11:34,085
- Oh, come on.
- Hey!

311
00:11:34,152 --> 00:11:35,287
OH, DANIEL

312
00:11:35,353 --> 00:11:36,688
THERE HE GOES AGAIN!

313
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:39,858
- Hey! These aren't long johns!
- What's with you?

314
00:11:39,924 --> 00:11:40,925
THEY'RE NOT LONG JOHNS

315
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:43,328
We've all been avoiding that subject.

316
00:11:43,528 --> 00:11:46,298
I'll have you know
this is a trendy look.

317
00:11:46,364 --> 00:11:48,133
Stay quiet, will you?

318
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:49,868
INTIMIDATED

319
00:11:49,934 --> 00:11:50,935
MY ABS, WHAT A HEADACHE

320
00:11:51,002 --> 00:11:52,771
Not everyone can pull off that look.

321
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:55,507
- Please give me a heads-up.
- All right.

322
00:11:55,573 --> 00:11:57,709
I'll give you the zip-it sign.

323
00:11:58,209 --> 00:11:59,311
MS. LONG JOHNS GETS TO WORK

324
00:11:59,377 --> 00:12:00,979
- I hope you don't mind what I said.
- Oh, no.

325
00:12:01,046 --> 00:12:03,548
I'm in trouble.
It looks like long johns to me, too.

326
00:12:03,615 --> 00:12:05,083
- Enough with that!
- She's done it.

327
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:06,551
- It's all set.
- We're in the clear.

328
00:12:06,618 --> 00:12:07,619
- All set.
- Yeah.

329
00:12:07,686 --> 00:12:09,187
I didn't say anything.
We're good now.

330
00:12:09,688 --> 00:12:10,789
Great.

331
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:11,856
Well done.

332
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:13,491
AFTER THE LONG JOHN FIASCO

333
00:12:13,558 --> 00:12:15,193
KEUN-SUK RECEIVES A TEXT

334
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:16,528
Hey, that was fun.

335
00:12:17,629 --> 00:12:19,364
Hold on, I have news to share.

336
00:12:19,964 --> 00:12:21,032
- What?
- What is it?

337
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:23,335
I got a text just now.

338
00:12:23,735 --> 00:12:24,936
- What does it say?
- About what?

339
00:12:25,003 --> 00:12:26,304
- Hey.
- What's up?

340
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:27,972
Did you get matched?

341
00:12:28,973 --> 00:12:31,009
COULD THIS BE ABOUT THE GROUP DATE?

342
00:12:31,076 --> 00:12:33,578
LUNCHTIME EARLIER TODAY

343
00:12:34,112 --> 00:12:36,681
SOO-JIN SHARED GROUP DATE OPTIONS
FOR DANIEL'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL

344
00:12:37,048 --> 00:12:39,250
OH, MY

345
00:12:39,918 --> 00:12:43,588
POTTERY DATES ARE
THE HOTTEST THESE DAYS

346
00:12:43,988 --> 00:12:47,225
HE'S READY TO CRAFT HIS LOVE

347
00:12:47,425 --> 00:12:49,861
Why don't the three of us
sign up together?

348
00:12:49,928 --> 00:12:52,897
- I can be your wingman.
- You sure?

349
00:12:52,964 --> 00:12:53,965
- Join us, Jae-hyeon.
- Okay.

350
00:12:54,032 --> 00:12:55,800
- Really?
- Here's the funny part.

351
00:12:56,201 --> 00:12:59,404
BUT THE THREE MEN
ARE NOT GUARANTEED A DATE!

352
00:12:59,471 --> 00:13:01,740
THE ORGANIZER PAIRS UP PARTICIPANTS
BASED ON THEIR PREFERENCES!

353
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,310
BEWARE OF NOT MAKING THE CUT

354
00:13:05,643 --> 00:13:06,845
- Did you hear from them?
- Really?

355
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:08,346
- This is insane.
- "Will our connection

356
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:09,414
have a beautiful shape, too?"

357
00:13:11,649 --> 00:13:13,318
SECOND-HAND THRILLS

358
00:13:14,619 --> 00:13:15,954
What's this?

359
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:19,491
"We confirm your attendance
for the pottery date."

360
00:13:19,557 --> 00:13:20,558
KEUN-SUK GOT A TEXT FIRST

361
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:21,793
WHAT ABOUT ME?

362
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:22,894
Should I get my phone?

363
00:13:22,961 --> 00:13:24,562
- I'll go get it.
- Go ahead.

364
00:13:25,230 --> 00:13:27,399
"Hope you have a special time
getting to know your partner

365
00:13:27,465 --> 00:13:29,234
as you slowly craft
your pottery piece."

366
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,935
- "Please prepare..."
- Wait.

367
00:13:31,002 --> 00:13:32,337
Okay, hurry back.

368
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:34,839
SCURRYING OFF

369
00:13:35,373 --> 00:13:37,842
IN A HURRY

370
00:13:37,909 --> 00:13:41,980
SO MUCH ENTHUSIASM
FOR A SUPPOSEDLY WINGMAN

371
00:13:42,046 --> 00:13:43,715
You guys are all pretty into it.

372
00:13:44,816 --> 00:13:47,352
It's pretty exciting
to get the text just the day before.

373
00:13:48,653 --> 00:13:49,687
Did you get the text?

374
00:13:50,422 --> 00:13:51,990
- Did you get a text?
- No.

375
00:13:52,056 --> 00:13:53,091
You didn't get it?

376
00:13:54,292 --> 00:13:56,027
What if Keun-suk alone gets it?

377
00:13:56,094 --> 00:13:57,228
Just me?

378
00:13:57,295 --> 00:13:58,363
OH, NO

379
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:00,765
Hold on.
Not everyone gets matched, right?

380
00:14:00,832 --> 00:14:01,933
That's right.

381
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,134
That's true.

382
00:14:03,201 --> 00:14:05,069
- Did you guys all get the text?
- Wait.

383
00:14:05,136 --> 00:14:06,704
- Have you checked your phone?
- Not yet.

384
00:14:06,771 --> 00:14:07,772
- You haven't?
- No.

385
00:14:07,839 --> 00:14:09,340
I just brought it without checking.

386
00:14:09,574 --> 00:14:10,875
- Did you get a text?
- So?

387
00:14:10,942 --> 00:14:11,943
ET TU, JAE-HYEON?

388
00:14:12,243 --> 00:14:13,344
I haven't gotten a text.

389
00:14:13,411 --> 00:14:14,846
- No?
- I haven't received it yet.

390
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:16,514
You know what?

391
00:14:17,081 --> 00:14:19,717
It won't be so terrible
if Jae-hyeon also doesn't get it.

392
00:14:19,784 --> 00:14:21,319
If Daniel were
the only one cast aside

393
00:14:21,386 --> 00:14:23,721
- I'd feel terrible.
- it'd be awkward.

394
00:14:23,955 --> 00:14:25,123
Let's not think that way.

395
00:14:25,190 --> 00:14:27,058
If Daniel and Jae-hyeon
didn't get matched

396
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:28,960
I'd give up the group date.

397
00:14:29,761 --> 00:14:31,029
- Come on.
- But why?

398
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:33,565
He's acting up again,
trying to look cool.

399
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:38,269
Why don't I pop by my own place
for a couple of hours tomorrow?

400
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:41,206
Then I'll pretend to be you
and take your spot.

401
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,442
HE'S DOWN WITH WHATEVER
SO LONG AS HE GETS THE DATE

402
00:14:44,509 --> 00:14:46,478
- Don't forget his jacket.
- I'll wear it.

403
00:14:46,544 --> 00:14:47,912
With Keun-suk's jacket on...

404
00:14:47,979 --> 00:14:49,214
I think I get how it works.

405
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,949
The organizers shared your info

406
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:53,017
and one of the women said
they were interested in Keun-suk.

407
00:14:53,084 --> 00:14:54,586
- Someone called dibs?
- That's what's up?

408
00:14:54,652 --> 00:14:55,653
That must be it, right?

409
00:14:55,854 --> 00:14:58,389
- Did they say who picked you?
- No.

410
00:14:58,456 --> 00:15:02,026
The text only mentions the location,
the time, and a few instructions.

411
00:15:02,327 --> 00:15:03,528
What kind of instructions?

412
00:15:04,095 --> 00:15:05,263
"Be open-hearted

413
00:15:05,330 --> 00:15:06,464
have your nails clipped short

414
00:15:06,531 --> 00:15:07,932
and bring one item to represent you."

415
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,335
What are you going to bring?

416
00:15:10,401 --> 00:15:11,703
That idea is awesome.

417
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:15,240
You have to be there to find out.
It doesn't say much.

418
00:15:15,306 --> 00:15:17,842
Are the nicknames supposed
to be kept a secret?

419
00:15:17,909 --> 00:15:20,078
THEY CAN'T HELP
BUT CHECK THEIR PHONES REPEATEDLY

420
00:15:20,411 --> 00:15:22,046
Maybe their texts are being screened?

421
00:15:22,914 --> 00:15:23,915
Well...

422
00:15:25,116 --> 00:15:26,518
Enjoy your date tomorrow, Keun-suk.

423
00:15:27,552 --> 00:15:30,288
Are you sure you'd be cool
if you were the only one left out?

424
00:15:31,089 --> 00:15:33,558
Well, let's suppose

425
00:15:33,625 --> 00:15:35,627
that I don't get matched
for the group date tomorrow.

426
00:15:37,395 --> 00:15:38,563
HESITATES

427
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:39,831
Let's...

428
00:15:41,032 --> 00:15:42,166
go for a walk with me.

429
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:43,801
UTTER SILENCE

430
00:15:43,868 --> 00:15:45,603
Let's go for a walk with me.

431
00:15:45,670 --> 00:15:47,906
AVOIDS EYE CONTACT

432
00:15:47,972 --> 00:15:49,541
Make a little sacrifice for me.

433
00:15:49,607 --> 00:15:50,608
SUDDENLY BUSY

434
00:15:50,675 --> 00:15:52,777
SUDDENLY TAKING A BIG BITE

435
00:15:52,844 --> 00:15:54,779
SUDDENLY GRAVE

436
00:15:54,846 --> 00:15:59,050
SURPRISINGLY, NO ONE PAID
ANY ATTENTION TO HIS COMMENT

437
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:00,718
I didn't get the text either, Daniel.

438
00:16:00,785 --> 00:16:02,086
- You didn't?
- No.

439
00:16:02,153 --> 00:16:03,821
Don't be like that, guys.

440
00:16:03,888 --> 00:16:06,190
The organizers might still be waiting
to hear from the ladies.

441
00:16:06,491 --> 00:16:08,826
- No way, it's pretty late already.
- What time is it?

442
00:16:08,893 --> 00:16:10,562
It's 8:15 p.m. It's late.

443
00:16:11,396 --> 00:16:14,232
Is it really?
It's unexpectedly tricky to attend.

444
00:16:14,432 --> 00:16:16,034
This is pretty upsetting.

445
00:16:16,701 --> 00:16:19,003
- It's ruining my mood already.
- It is, isn't it?

446
00:16:19,771 --> 00:16:22,440
WHAT A WAY TO MAKE ONE GO SILENT

447
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:24,375
You guys suggested that I use

448
00:16:24,742 --> 00:16:27,345
the photo that I took in the van.

449
00:16:27,745 --> 00:16:30,481
I actually shot
two photos in the van.

450
00:16:30,715 --> 00:16:33,384
I personally prefer funny pics
showing my nostrils

451
00:16:33,451 --> 00:16:34,452
so I used a photo that did.

452
00:16:34,986 --> 00:16:36,988
- The one that showed your nostrils?
- Yeah.

453
00:16:37,288 --> 00:16:38,289
HEY, GIVE UP AND FIND PEACE

454
00:16:38,356 --> 00:16:40,124
- Let me have a look.
- What?

455
00:16:40,191 --> 00:16:41,960
- So you uploaded this picture?
- Yeah.

456
00:16:42,427 --> 00:16:43,494
So you used this?

457
00:16:43,928 --> 00:16:46,097
This really isn't...

458
00:16:46,798 --> 00:16:47,799
Let me see.

459
00:16:47,865 --> 00:16:49,367
WINGMAN 2
FOUND PEACE AFTER GIVING UP

460
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:51,402
Then again...

461
00:16:51,903 --> 00:16:52,904
Why didn't you...

462
00:16:53,171 --> 00:16:55,073
- I got the text!
- You did?

463
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:57,175
I GOT THE TEXT!
I'M GOING TO THE GROUP DATE!

464
00:16:57,642 --> 00:17:00,144
GLAD YOU GOT IT, BUDDY!

465
00:17:00,612 --> 00:17:02,213
- Jae-hyeon.
- Congratulations.

466
00:17:02,847 --> 00:17:04,282
CRESTFALLEN

467
00:17:04,349 --> 00:17:05,683
- Jae-hyeon.
- Yes?

468
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:06,784
Can't you read the room?

469
00:17:07,452 --> 00:17:08,453
RIGHT...

470
00:17:08,519 --> 00:17:09,654
Keep your wits about you.

471
00:17:09,854 --> 00:17:12,190
- I got too excited.
- You'll get it soon, Daniel.

472
00:17:12,256 --> 00:17:14,092
Hold on just a second.

473
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:16,227
This is my House Squad Goal

474
00:17:16,294 --> 00:17:18,062
but everyone got matched except me.

475
00:17:18,129 --> 00:17:20,331
Let's give it time, okay?

476
00:17:20,531 --> 00:17:22,867
It's my House Squad Goal.

477
00:17:22,934 --> 00:17:24,602
They're just my wingmen.

478
00:17:25,069 --> 00:17:27,872
WE WERE GOING AS MORAL SUPPORT...

479
00:17:28,239 --> 00:17:29,674
You'll get it soon, Daniel.

480
00:17:29,741 --> 00:17:31,409
You might be the last to get it

481
00:17:31,476 --> 00:17:33,011
- as the finale.
- You're the male lead.

482
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:35,413
THOSE COMMENTS
AREN'T DOING IT FOR HIM

483
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:37,315
STUDIES HIS FACE

484
00:17:37,382 --> 00:17:39,917
STUDIES HIS FACE, TOO

485
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:42,487
LONELY

486
00:17:42,553 --> 00:17:44,188
- What did your text say?
- The same thing.

487
00:17:44,255 --> 00:17:46,958
It's from the organizers.

488
00:17:47,025 --> 00:17:48,259
Darn it.

489
00:17:49,127 --> 00:17:50,528
- What's the matter?
- It's nothing.

490
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:54,499
HE WAS REALLY LOOKING FORWARD
TO THE GROUP DATE

491
00:17:54,565 --> 00:17:56,267
It's nothing. Let me fix this.

492
00:17:56,334 --> 00:17:57,535
You never know, right?

493
00:17:57,602 --> 00:17:59,203
I'm sure someone

494
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:00,605
- will like my funny picture.
- Sure.

495
00:18:00,672 --> 00:18:02,573
There are so many people out there

496
00:18:02,974 --> 00:18:04,042
across the country.

497
00:18:04,108 --> 00:18:05,109
You're right.

498
00:18:05,176 --> 00:18:06,978
If I don't get matched

499
00:18:07,045 --> 00:18:08,713
could any of you spare
some time for me?

500
00:18:09,247 --> 00:18:10,782
Could any of you spare
some time for me?

501
00:18:10,848 --> 00:18:12,417
RECRUITING A HOUSEMATE
FOR A WALK AGAIN

502
00:18:13,051 --> 00:18:15,086
BUSILY TAKES A BIG BITE

503
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:17,221
TAKES A BIG BITE

504
00:18:17,288 --> 00:18:19,023
Why are you eating all of a sudden?

505
00:18:19,090 --> 00:18:20,091
It's good.

506
00:18:20,158 --> 00:18:21,759
- You bet.
- It's awesome.

507
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:24,762
I can't believe it tastes so good.

508
00:18:24,962 --> 00:18:26,364
- It has a restaurant quality.
- Totally.

509
00:18:26,431 --> 00:18:28,733
- For sure.
- Keun-suk did an amazing job.

510
00:18:31,169 --> 00:18:32,370
Soo-jin.

511
00:18:33,071 --> 00:18:34,706
PRETENDS NOT TO HAVE SEEN HIM

512
00:18:34,772 --> 00:18:35,773
- Do-yeon.
- Yes?

513
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,075
I used a good sauce.

514
00:18:37,141 --> 00:18:38,576
- So true.
- It's delicious.

515
00:18:38,643 --> 00:18:40,511
- They'll text you.
- I'm sure they will.

516
00:18:41,846 --> 00:18:44,048
- Get over there even if they don't.
- Yeah.

517
00:18:44,348 --> 00:18:46,617
I love you so much, my friends.

518
00:18:47,785 --> 00:18:48,920
Daniel.

519
00:18:48,986 --> 00:18:50,688
- There was a ten-minute gap.
- There was.

520
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:51,956
I'm sure you'll get yours soon.

521
00:18:52,023 --> 00:18:53,224
All right.

522
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:54,592
Understood.

523
00:18:54,892 --> 00:18:55,893
I'm sure of it.

524
00:18:57,695 --> 00:18:58,696
Anyhow...

525
00:19:00,164 --> 00:19:01,799
I take it you're all busy tomorrow?

526
00:19:02,633 --> 00:19:04,335
This pork cutlets...

527
00:19:04,669 --> 00:19:05,937
- It's great.
- Who wants some more?

528
00:19:06,571 --> 00:19:07,572
It's delicious.

529
00:19:07,638 --> 00:19:09,373
I made a commitment.

530
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,175
- I can't exactly bail, right?
- No.

531
00:19:11,876 --> 00:19:13,277
There goes our friendship.

532
00:19:13,344 --> 00:19:15,546
We have to get you there.

533
00:19:15,613 --> 00:19:16,614
Get me where?

534
00:19:16,681 --> 00:19:18,616
- It's your House Squad Goal.
- Exactly.

535
00:19:18,683 --> 00:19:20,485
- We'll help you realize that dream.
- Of course.

536
00:19:20,551 --> 00:19:22,386
- Yes.
- All right.

537
00:19:22,587 --> 00:19:24,188
- I achieved my goal today.
- It's good, right?

538
00:19:26,991 --> 00:19:29,494
- Did you get your text?
- Is that it?

539
00:19:30,695 --> 00:19:31,929
IS IT THE TEXT

540
00:19:31,996 --> 00:19:34,465
THAT EVERYONE HAS BEEN WAITING FOR?

541
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:37,468
It's a text from my dad.

542
00:19:37,935 --> 00:19:39,303
I SEE...

543
00:19:39,370 --> 00:19:40,872
You're a kind son.
Text him back right away.

544
00:19:40,938 --> 00:19:42,540
What do you guys talk about?

545
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,710
"I want you to know

546
00:19:45,777 --> 00:19:49,013
that your brother's family and I
are celebrating the day you were born

547
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:53,151
around 12 a.m on February 22, 1986.

548
00:19:53,217 --> 00:19:54,318
Congratulations.

549
00:19:58,589 --> 00:20:02,059
May the Lord keep you in good health
and bless you with love this year.

550
00:20:02,393 --> 00:20:03,961
I'll pray for you. Your dad."

551
00:20:04,028 --> 00:20:05,363
My gosh.

552
00:20:05,429 --> 00:20:06,931
A HEARTFELT MESSAGE FROM FATHER

553
00:20:06,998 --> 00:20:10,034
- It's clear he loves you very much.
- He's so romantic.

554
00:20:10,101 --> 00:20:11,936
You born at twelve o'clock sharp?

555
00:20:12,003 --> 00:20:13,104
That's a new detail for me, too.

556
00:20:13,171 --> 00:20:15,072
- Really?
- How peculiar.

557
00:20:15,139 --> 00:20:17,241
What do you usually do
on your birthday?

558
00:20:17,308 --> 00:20:19,076
- Do you spend it with your family?
- Me?

559
00:20:19,143 --> 00:20:20,578
No, I spend the day alone.

560
00:20:21,112 --> 00:20:22,313
- What about last year?
- What about last year?

561
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:23,381
Jinx.

562
00:20:24,115 --> 00:20:26,317
- Just one year ago, right?
- Yeah.

563
00:20:27,652 --> 00:20:28,986
- Nothing much.
- You had work, right?

564
00:20:29,053 --> 00:20:31,622
- I probably had a shoot.
- I see.

565
00:20:32,023 --> 00:20:34,125
It's been ages
since I celebrated my birthday.

566
00:20:34,792 --> 00:20:38,029
When was your loneliest birthday?

567
00:20:38,396 --> 00:20:40,498
THE LONELIEST ONE?

568
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:42,600
Why would you bring him down?

569
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:43,668
Please don't tell me

570
00:20:43,734 --> 00:20:46,537
you're worried tomorrow
might be the loneliest day for him.

571
00:20:46,604 --> 00:20:47,972
Come on, we'll be there.

572
00:20:48,573 --> 00:20:50,107
I don't think I've been that excited.

573
00:20:50,174 --> 00:20:52,109
I do remember one birthday.

574
00:20:52,176 --> 00:20:54,478
It was during the early years
in elementary school.

575
00:20:56,314 --> 00:20:58,049
Back then, my family was living

576
00:20:58,115 --> 00:21:02,353
in a house with a detached toilet
heated by coal briquettes or LP gas.

577
00:21:03,721 --> 00:21:07,291
My dad brought a mocha mousse cake.

578
00:21:07,358 --> 00:21:09,594
- The old classic using butter cream.
- I know what it is.

579
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:12,964
He bought a small cake

580
00:21:13,030 --> 00:21:14,532
and a LEGO set for me.

581
00:21:15,199 --> 00:21:16,834
It was a hut for pirates.

582
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:19,103
A small kit
that only costs 4,900 won.

583
00:21:19,170 --> 00:21:22,406
It was just a little party
with my brother and my dad.

584
00:21:22,473 --> 00:21:23,741
That stuck with me.

585
00:21:24,475 --> 00:21:26,410
<i>We had the photos developed</i>

586
00:21:26,477 --> 00:21:28,446
<i>- from the film camera.</i>
<i>- Right.</i>

587
00:21:28,512 --> 00:21:29,747
<i>- Do you still have them?</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

588
00:21:29,814 --> 00:21:31,983
<i>My mother passed away</i>
<i>when I was young.</i>

589
00:21:32,049 --> 00:21:33,050
<i>I only had my dad.</i>

590
00:21:33,117 --> 00:21:36,721
HIS FATHER MADE A VALIANT EFFORT
TO FILL THE VOID LEFT BY HIS MOTHER

591
00:21:36,787 --> 00:21:38,689
The grandest birthday party...

592
00:21:38,756 --> 00:21:40,391
Well, that's the most memorable one.

593
00:21:40,458 --> 00:21:42,960
- It was most memorable?
- I don't recall much in detail...

594
00:21:43,027 --> 00:21:45,096
But you remember
your family's presence.

595
00:21:45,162 --> 00:21:48,833
HE REMEMBERS THAT DAY HE SHARED
WITH HIS FAMILY ABOUT 30 YEARS AGO

596
00:21:50,601 --> 00:21:54,739
Did you usually spend
your birthday with your family?

597
00:21:54,805 --> 00:21:56,974
Since we all lived together
when I was young.

598
00:21:58,009 --> 00:22:00,144
I've gotten comfortable being alone.
Isn't it the same with you guys?

599
00:22:00,211 --> 00:22:03,414
At this age,
birthdays aren't that special.

600
00:22:04,048 --> 00:22:05,783
When you live alone

601
00:22:05,850 --> 00:22:08,452
you don't tend to throw parties.

602
00:22:08,653 --> 00:22:11,455
Don't you spend the day
with your friends?

603
00:22:11,656 --> 00:22:12,890
Not really.

604
00:22:13,391 --> 00:22:15,293
- I just have my dinner, and...
- Yeah, just that.

605
00:22:15,359 --> 00:22:16,861
It's not like that for me.

606
00:22:17,228 --> 00:22:18,562
- How so?
- What do you do?

607
00:22:18,629 --> 00:22:23,100
I happily prepare a feast
so I can share it with my friends.

608
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:24,201
I SEE

609
00:22:24,268 --> 00:22:25,303
For example

610
00:22:25,369 --> 00:22:26,704
I'll hand out homemade seaweed soup

611
00:22:26,771 --> 00:22:30,207
packaged in a takeaway cup
right from the entrance.

612
00:22:31,208 --> 00:22:33,611
It's not about me having fun.

613
00:22:33,678 --> 00:22:36,647
It's more of setting up a place
for my friends to hang out and enjoy.

614
00:22:36,714 --> 00:22:38,616
- So you treat them in a way?
- Yes.

615
00:22:38,683 --> 00:22:41,185
It's my way of thanking them
for staying by my side.

616
00:22:41,686 --> 00:22:43,321
For more than a decade

617
00:22:43,387 --> 00:22:46,157
I've always made the same wish
when I blew out the candles.

618
00:22:46,223 --> 00:22:48,025
- Just one?
- Yes, the exact same one.

619
00:22:48,092 --> 00:22:49,293
- With my eyes shut...
- I'm curious.

620
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:50,361
Can you share it?

621
00:22:50,528 --> 00:22:52,697
"Please let my friends
gathered here today

622
00:22:52,763 --> 00:22:55,466
join me again
on my birthday next year."

623
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:57,702
- That's a tough order.
- You bet it is.

624
00:22:57,768 --> 00:22:59,236
- So true.
- It's just not easy.

625
00:22:59,303 --> 00:23:02,306
I hope you'll all come
to my birthday party this year.

626
00:23:02,373 --> 00:23:03,407
- When is it?
- Really?

627
00:23:03,474 --> 00:23:04,475
We have time. It's in August.

628
00:23:04,542 --> 00:23:05,810
Thank goodness.

629
00:23:07,144 --> 00:23:09,213
WHAT A LONG-LASTING SIDE-EFFECT

630
00:23:09,580 --> 00:23:11,916
- I'd love to have your seaweed soup.
- Sure.

631
00:23:11,983 --> 00:23:13,884
When exactly is it?
In early August or late August?

632
00:23:13,951 --> 00:23:14,986
It's the 4th.

633
00:23:15,052 --> 00:23:16,220
- August 4th.
- It's early August.

634
00:23:16,921 --> 00:23:18,823
I'll probably be busy.

635
00:23:18,889 --> 00:23:20,791
IN A CRABBY MOOD
FOR NOT RECEIVING A TEXT

636
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:21,892
You went too far there.

637
00:23:21,959 --> 00:23:22,994
I'M UPSET

638
00:23:23,060 --> 00:23:25,162
I WAS JUST MESSING WITH YOU

639
00:23:25,229 --> 00:23:27,565
Honestly though if I don't...

640
00:23:30,468 --> 00:23:31,969
- Honestly...
- Yes?

641
00:23:33,137 --> 00:23:34,271
Let's just say

642
00:23:34,338 --> 00:23:35,940
- I don't get matched for real.
- Yes.

643
00:23:36,507 --> 00:23:38,576
- Wait, no.
- That made you trip over words?

644
00:23:38,642 --> 00:23:40,945
- That's all he's thinking about.
- There's always next week's date.

645
00:23:41,012 --> 00:23:42,480
JUST HEAR ME OUT

646
00:23:42,546 --> 00:23:43,914
Let's say I don't get matched.

647
00:23:43,981 --> 00:23:47,218
HE CAN'T HELP BUT THINK
ABOUT THE WORST-CASE SCENARIO

648
00:23:47,284 --> 00:23:48,719
Tomorrow's my birthday.

649
00:23:49,620 --> 00:23:51,022
You know it's my House Squad Goal

650
00:23:51,088 --> 00:23:52,990
to enjoy a meal and a slow dance

651
00:23:53,057 --> 00:23:54,458
at a restaurant, right?

652
00:23:54,525 --> 00:23:56,727
Can you help me realize that dream?

653
00:23:57,361 --> 00:23:58,562
Let's be real, Daniel.

654
00:23:58,629 --> 00:24:00,664
Do you honestly think
we won't give you a dance

655
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:01,832
after being rejected big time?

656
00:24:01,899 --> 00:24:02,900
Are we fake friends or what?

657
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:04,001
- Rejected?
- Rejected?

658
00:24:04,068 --> 00:24:05,069
Did you say rejected?

659
00:24:05,136 --> 00:24:06,337
- I can't believe this.
- Come on.

660
00:24:06,537 --> 00:24:07,905
Rejected?
He hasn't been on a date yet.

661
00:24:07,972 --> 00:24:09,306
- Hey.
- Come on.

662
00:24:09,373 --> 00:24:11,976
I only said that because
he hasn't gotten the text yet.

663
00:24:12,043 --> 00:24:13,377
It's just one possible scenario.

664
00:24:13,444 --> 00:24:14,979
Should I give them a call, Daniel?

665
00:24:15,513 --> 00:24:17,181
- You mean the organizers?
- I can call them to ask

666
00:24:17,248 --> 00:24:19,750
if Writer Choi didn't get matched.

667
00:24:20,051 --> 00:24:21,052
No.

668
00:24:21,685 --> 00:24:22,853
Let's just enjoy our dinner.

669
00:24:23,187 --> 00:24:24,655
He'd feel more mortified.

670
00:24:24,722 --> 00:24:26,057
- Yeah.
- I guess I shouldn't, then.

671
00:24:26,123 --> 00:24:27,458
SOMEWHAT AT PEACE

672
00:24:27,525 --> 00:24:29,160
Maybe you picked the wrong date?

673
00:24:29,226 --> 00:24:31,429
- Check if you picked a date in 2027.
- Maybe you chose next week.

674
00:24:31,495 --> 00:24:32,496
Hey, guys!

675
00:24:32,563 --> 00:24:33,764
- Did you get it?
- I got it, too!

676
00:24:33,831 --> 00:24:35,066
IS IT THE REAL THING THIS TIME?

677
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:37,068
THE SPECTATORS CAUSE A BIGGER FUSS

678
00:24:37,134 --> 00:24:38,936
- Hang on.
- So you got it!

679
00:24:39,336 --> 00:24:40,604
- I knew it.
- I got it.

680
00:24:40,671 --> 00:24:43,307
"Will our connection
have a beautiful shape, too?

681
00:24:43,808 --> 00:24:45,943
We confirm your attendance
for the pottery date."

682
00:24:46,010 --> 00:24:47,011
All right.

683
00:24:47,078 --> 00:24:48,412
I knew he'd get matched.

684
00:24:48,479 --> 00:24:49,914
So we're all set.

685
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:51,348
We're all good now.

686
00:24:51,415 --> 00:24:52,650
- Congrats.
- He got a spot.

687
00:24:52,716 --> 00:24:53,717
- Congrats.
- Congrats!

688
00:24:53,784 --> 00:24:55,386
All right. Thank you, guys.

689
00:24:55,653 --> 00:24:57,188
FINALLY SMILING AGAIN

690
00:24:57,254 --> 00:24:58,956
SO SIMPLE

691
00:24:59,523 --> 00:25:02,359
We won't have to deal
with surly Daniel anymore.

692
00:25:03,094 --> 00:25:04,829
That was a narrow escape.

693
00:25:05,896 --> 00:25:07,531
- Guys.
- He would've kept at it.

694
00:25:07,598 --> 00:25:08,799
The dinner is excellent.

695
00:25:09,266 --> 00:25:11,202
FEELS LIKE THE KING OF THE WORLD

696
00:25:11,402 --> 00:25:13,737
I'll go with you
on that walk tomorrow.

697
00:25:13,938 --> 00:25:15,272
- No.
- During the day.

698
00:25:15,339 --> 00:25:17,007
I have to get to my date by 12 p.m.

699
00:25:17,074 --> 00:25:18,075
Really?

700
00:25:18,142 --> 00:25:20,778
HE'S SO TRANSPARENT, RIGHT?

701
00:25:20,845 --> 00:25:23,247
- I can't wait.
- You want to watch, right?

702
00:25:23,314 --> 00:25:25,549
I wish there were cameras
I could watch live.

703
00:25:25,749 --> 00:25:27,651
Actually, there's one thing

704
00:25:28,285 --> 00:25:29,553
I haven't shared with you guys.

705
00:25:29,954 --> 00:25:31,021
- What is it?
- About what?

706
00:25:31,589 --> 00:25:32,723
My suit arrived.

707
00:25:32,790 --> 00:25:34,792
When?

708
00:25:34,859 --> 00:25:36,227
- So soon?
- Yeah.

709
00:25:36,293 --> 00:25:38,395
- They arrived...
- Are you going to wear it tomorrow?

710
00:25:38,696 --> 00:25:40,531
But you don't want
to look too formal, right?

711
00:25:40,598 --> 00:25:41,999
That's what I'm worried about.

712
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,468
Before all this

713
00:25:44,535 --> 00:25:46,437
- it's your birthday tomorrow.
- Yeah.

714
00:25:47,271 --> 00:25:50,708
I wanted to give you
a birthday present.

715
00:25:51,208 --> 00:25:53,978
DID DA-HEE PREPARE A BIRTHDAY GIFT?

716
00:25:54,578 --> 00:25:56,013
I kind of prepared something.

717
00:25:56,547 --> 00:25:58,582
When we're done eating

718
00:25:58,916 --> 00:26:01,652
can you spare me a little time?

719
00:26:01,719 --> 00:26:03,020
Can you spare me a little time?

720
00:26:03,087 --> 00:26:04,421
Did you have a crush on me?

721
00:26:06,290 --> 00:26:08,325
SQUEEZES HER EYES SHUT

722
00:26:08,392 --> 00:26:10,461
- My gosh!
- Maybe it's a birthday beating?

723
00:26:12,196 --> 00:26:13,464
- Da-hee.
- What?

724
00:26:14,798 --> 00:26:16,667
- You're just...
- Actually

725
00:26:16,734 --> 00:26:21,772
Da-hee sent me a text
when everyone was asleep at night.

726
00:26:21,839 --> 00:26:24,475
- At night?
- She asked for my advice.

727
00:26:24,542 --> 00:26:25,576
Really?

728
00:26:25,643 --> 00:26:27,745
AMAZED SIGHS AND CHATTERS

729
00:26:27,811 --> 00:26:29,680
- She wanted my take on things.
- So cool.

730
00:26:30,114 --> 00:26:32,249
Will you be there
for the pottery date tomorrow?

731
00:26:33,150 --> 00:26:34,185
Maybe.

732
00:26:34,251 --> 00:26:35,286
What's this?

733
00:26:35,586 --> 00:26:37,254
OH, MY

734
00:26:37,588 --> 00:26:39,123
Gosh, my heart is racing.

735
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:41,091
- You're the best.
- What's going on?

736
00:26:41,158 --> 00:26:43,627
Can someone tell me what's going on?

737
00:26:43,694 --> 00:26:46,964
It's just a little something
I wanted to do for you.

738
00:26:47,031 --> 00:26:48,732
- Really?
- From the bottom of my heart.

739
00:26:48,799 --> 00:26:49,800
Yeah.

740
00:26:50,167 --> 00:26:51,635
From the bottom of my heart.

741
00:26:51,936 --> 00:26:53,637
- That date might not be necessary.
- Hey.

742
00:26:53,704 --> 00:26:55,940
Cancel that date. Say, "Sorry,
but I found my soulmate."

743
00:26:56,006 --> 00:26:57,641
- Cut it out and clean...
- Should I?

744
00:26:57,708 --> 00:26:59,043
Say, "Sorry,
but I found my soulmate."

745
00:26:59,109 --> 00:27:01,912
Cut it out and clean
if you guys are done eating.

746
00:27:02,179 --> 00:27:04,281
- Why are you acting so awkward?
- This is gold.

747
00:27:04,348 --> 00:27:06,417
- Should we give you some privacy?
- Why are you stuttering?

748
00:27:06,483 --> 00:27:09,153
DANIEL'S BODY HAS ALWAYS BEEN
TURNED TOWARD DO-YEON

749
00:27:09,220 --> 00:27:11,555
BUT HE'S NOW FACING DA-HEE

750
00:27:11,622 --> 00:27:12,623
I was just messing with you.

751
00:27:12,690 --> 00:27:13,691
Guys.

752
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:15,159
This is clearly a guy who's in love.

753
00:27:16,093 --> 00:27:17,094
Tell me if I'm wrong.

754
00:27:17,461 --> 00:27:21,298
DA-HEE...

755
00:27:27,271 --> 00:27:29,640
TAKES IT FURTHER

756
00:27:29,707 --> 00:27:32,042
I'm tempted to give you a slap.

757
00:27:33,310 --> 00:27:35,512
- It's so touching.
- It's so weird.

758
00:27:35,579 --> 00:27:36,614
Applause, everyone.

759
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:38,015
A STRANGE ENERGY FILLS UP
GUGI-DONG HOUSE

760
00:27:38,082 --> 00:27:39,083
All right, then.

761
00:27:39,383 --> 00:27:41,151
- Let's head downstairs.
- Okay.

762
00:27:41,218 --> 00:27:42,820
Change into your suit
and then join us.

763
00:27:43,821 --> 00:27:46,590
DANIEL IS FINALLY TRYING
ON HIS FIRST-EVER BESPOKE SUIT

764
00:27:46,657 --> 00:27:48,025
My gosh.

765
00:27:48,325 --> 00:27:49,493
This is incredible.

766
00:27:50,694 --> 00:27:51,862
Just incredible.

767
00:27:53,297 --> 00:27:54,932
My gosh.

768
00:27:56,934 --> 00:27:59,703
<i>It felt so awkward at first.</i>

769
00:28:00,237 --> 00:28:02,773
AWKWARD

770
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:04,441
<i>But after I put on the full set</i>

771
00:28:04,508 --> 00:28:06,210
<i>I found that I liked</i>
<i>the color very much.</i>

772
00:28:06,477 --> 00:28:07,511
<i>It was great.</i>

773
00:28:08,679 --> 00:28:10,714
WHILE DANIEL IS HAPPY

774
00:28:10,781 --> 00:28:13,717
EVERYONE IN THE LIVING ROOM
IS LOOKING SERIOUS

775
00:28:14,385 --> 00:28:18,289
THE HOUSEMATES LOOK
LIKE THEY'RE PLOTTING SOMETHING

776
00:28:18,756 --> 00:28:21,025
WHAT IS GOING ON?

777
00:28:21,492 --> 00:28:23,394
- I'm heading downstairs.
- All right!

778
00:28:23,861 --> 00:28:26,363
- I'm heading downstairs.
- Here he comes.

779
00:28:27,998 --> 00:28:29,033
Come on.

780
00:28:29,099 --> 00:28:31,101
HURRIEDLY CHANGING THE MOOD

781
00:28:32,403 --> 00:28:34,538
EVERYONE CHEERS

782
00:28:36,206 --> 00:28:39,109
TALL AND PROUD

783
00:28:39,576 --> 00:28:43,180
JOURNALISTS OF GUGI-DONG
TAKE PHOTOS NON-STOP

784
00:28:44,181 --> 00:28:48,052
THE SUIT FITS DANIEL PERFECTLY

785
00:28:48,686 --> 00:28:51,822
THE GIRLS ARE MOVED BY HIS LOOK

786
00:28:53,157 --> 00:28:54,491
It's so sleek!

787
00:28:54,558 --> 00:28:56,460
- You look great.
- So cool.

788
00:28:56,527 --> 00:28:58,662
- You look amazing.
- Is it okay?

789
00:28:59,229 --> 00:29:00,864
COMPARED TO MR. TAN A FEW DAYS AGO

790
00:29:00,931 --> 00:29:02,633
- You look amazing.
- Do I clean up nicely?

791
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:04,234
- Let me see.
- You look grand.

792
00:29:04,301 --> 00:29:07,738
It feels like
I'm at a movie screening.

793
00:29:07,805 --> 00:29:08,972
CHEERFUL SMILE AND HAND GESTURES

794
00:29:09,039 --> 00:29:10,974
Do I look okay?
What do you guys think?

795
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:12,343
- You look good.
- Really?

796
00:29:12,943 --> 00:29:14,878
- You look really fine.
- It suits you so well.

797
00:29:14,945 --> 00:29:16,213
- Really?
- Yes.

798
00:29:17,548 --> 00:29:21,885
MEANTIME, DA-HEE IS BUSY
WITH SOMETHING IN THE CORNER

799
00:29:22,519 --> 00:29:25,956
SWEET DA-HEE'S CHILLING SILENCE

800
00:29:26,623 --> 00:29:28,158
OH, RIGHT!

801
00:29:28,225 --> 00:29:30,160
- Guys, Da-hee prepared all this.
- What?

802
00:29:30,694 --> 00:29:31,962
- Da-hee prepared all this.
- What?

803
00:29:32,596 --> 00:29:34,998
These are all bespoke dress shoes.

804
00:29:35,532 --> 00:29:36,734
She needs to measure your size.

805
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:37,801
CHECK OUT DA-HEE'S PRESENT

806
00:29:37,868 --> 00:29:40,704
- She really went all out.
- It's amazing.

807
00:29:40,938 --> 00:29:43,607
We can't exactly visit
the shoemaker together.

808
00:29:43,674 --> 00:29:47,111
So I borrowed these samples specially
from a shoemaker I know.

809
00:29:47,177 --> 00:29:48,379
- Really?
- You bet.

810
00:29:48,445 --> 00:29:49,780
- No way.
- How thoughtful.

811
00:29:49,847 --> 00:29:52,082
So try these on and tell me

812
00:29:52,149 --> 00:29:53,884
- which design you like the best.
- Okay.

813
00:29:53,951 --> 00:29:55,686
I don't own dress shoes.

814
00:29:56,019 --> 00:29:57,020
You don't own them either?

815
00:29:57,087 --> 00:29:58,288
I don't.

816
00:29:58,355 --> 00:29:59,656
DA-HEE REMEMBERED
THIS PASSING COMMENT

817
00:29:59,890 --> 00:30:02,960
<i>When he said he didn't own a pair,</i>
<i>I thought, "I should get him one."</i>

818
00:30:04,261 --> 00:30:08,565
AT TIMES, SHE CAN BE HARD ON HIM

819
00:30:09,767 --> 00:30:13,670
BUT SHE TAKES EXCELLENT CARE OF HIM
AS IF HE'S HER OWN SIBLING

820
00:30:14,671 --> 00:30:16,173
- Let me tie these.
- No, it's okay.

821
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:17,541
They're meant to be worn unlaced.

822
00:30:17,608 --> 00:30:22,646
SWEET DA-HEE TAKES
PAINSTAKING CARE OF HER FRIENDS

823
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:26,216
<i>I had no knowledge</i>
<i>about men's dress shoes.</i>

824
00:30:28,619 --> 00:30:33,290
SHE PREPARED THESE SAMPLES
AFTER MAKING INQUIRIES HERSELF

825
00:30:33,357 --> 00:30:35,626
- You're so meticulous.
- Not at all.

826
00:30:35,692 --> 00:30:37,861
I honestly wanted to buy him a pair

827
00:30:37,928 --> 00:30:39,696
but I couldn't just get him

828
00:30:39,763 --> 00:30:41,932
- a ready-made pair.
- You want your present to count.

829
00:30:42,566 --> 00:30:44,401
I brought a pair
of all the available designs.

830
00:30:44,468 --> 00:30:45,636
This is insane.

831
00:30:46,503 --> 00:30:48,439
When we were at the tailor shop

832
00:30:48,505 --> 00:30:51,175
you said you wanted a pair
in dark brown.

833
00:30:51,241 --> 00:30:53,911
I brought a single shoe of each pair
just to check the color.

834
00:30:53,977 --> 00:30:55,746
THOUGHTFUL DA-HEE'S
METICULOUS PREPARATION

835
00:30:55,813 --> 00:30:57,815
The dark brown shoes look gorgeous.

836
00:30:57,881 --> 00:30:58,882
- It's crazy.
- There are samples.

837
00:30:59,349 --> 00:31:01,985
I can never be
as detail-oriented as Da-hee.

838
00:31:02,052 --> 00:31:03,921
- Me neither. I'm amazed.
- I'm mind-blown.

839
00:31:03,987 --> 00:31:05,489
I couldn't have thought
of such an idea.

840
00:31:05,556 --> 00:31:08,225
- Same.
- It never occurred to me.

841
00:31:08,292 --> 00:31:09,493
Let me see.

842
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:11,195
FIDGETY

843
00:31:11,261 --> 00:31:12,529
- Gosh, Da-hee.
- What?

844
00:31:12,596 --> 00:31:15,365
I'm not sure if I should receive
such a gift from you.

845
00:31:15,666 --> 00:31:17,868
I hope you enjoy wearing them.

846
00:31:17,935 --> 00:31:19,436
I'm sure I will.

847
00:31:19,636 --> 00:31:21,171
It kind of feels like that scene

848
00:31:21,572 --> 00:31:23,807
- where the Prince visits Cinderella
- Exactly.

849
00:31:23,874 --> 00:31:25,742
and helps her try on the glass shoe.

850
00:31:26,343 --> 00:31:27,478
I'm Cinderella in this scenario.

851
00:31:28,045 --> 00:31:29,213
DRESS SHOES INSTEAD OF A GLASS SHOE

852
00:31:29,279 --> 00:31:30,280
Thank you.

853
00:31:30,781 --> 00:31:32,449
- Leave your heel out.
- Just check the vibes.

854
00:31:32,516 --> 00:31:34,451
- It doesn't fit.
- This is the dark brown shoe.

855
00:31:35,185 --> 00:31:36,520
- I vote dark brown.
- DB?

856
00:31:36,587 --> 00:31:37,888
- Me too.
- Is it better?

857
00:31:37,955 --> 00:31:39,056
For your suit, yes.

858
00:31:39,122 --> 00:31:41,158
The color of your necktie
and that shoe match.

859
00:31:41,225 --> 00:31:42,326
A CLINCHER FROM THE EX-MODEL

860
00:31:42,392 --> 00:31:43,393
They're color-coordinated.

861
00:31:43,460 --> 00:31:44,895
- So DB it is.
- DB.

862
00:31:44,962 --> 00:31:45,963
DB, right?

863
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:47,831
I'll go with this one, then.

864
00:31:48,465 --> 00:31:51,101
Wouldn't it be great
if a tailor visited your home?

865
00:31:51,168 --> 00:31:52,169
How incredible is this?

866
00:31:52,236 --> 00:31:53,904
It'd cost a fortune
to have a shoemaker visit.

867
00:31:53,971 --> 00:31:56,473
- This never occurred to me.
- She brought the whole collection.

868
00:31:57,207 --> 00:31:59,042
- I can't contain my jealousy.
- What?

869
00:31:59,109 --> 00:32:00,511
- I'm so jealous.
- Me too.

870
00:32:02,212 --> 00:32:03,213
Like this?

871
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,215
- Yeah, just like this.
- Is this okay?

872
00:32:05,282 --> 00:32:07,317
<i>I didn't know</i>
<i>how to measure one's feet.</i>

873
00:32:07,384 --> 00:32:09,019
<i>So I learned from watching a video.</i>

874
00:32:11,021 --> 00:32:12,523
<i>She caught me completely off guard.</i>

875
00:32:12,856 --> 00:32:14,424
<i>It never occurred to me.</i>

876
00:32:15,092 --> 00:32:16,226
<i>I mean, seriously.</i>

877
00:32:16,293 --> 00:32:17,794
She's the famous Lee Da-hee.

878
00:32:18,629 --> 00:32:20,264
Who'd have thought she'd crouch down

879
00:32:20,330 --> 00:32:23,100
<i>and touch my feet</i>
<i>to measure the size?</i>

880
00:32:23,700 --> 00:32:25,235
<i>I felt so grateful and just...</i>

881
00:32:25,302 --> 00:32:27,037
<i>All kinds of thoughts</i>
<i>flitted through my mind.</i>

882
00:32:27,771 --> 00:32:31,174
<i>I enjoy going the extra mile</i>
<i>for my close friends.</i>

883
00:32:31,241 --> 00:32:33,877
<i>Seeing the recipient</i>
<i>appreciating my efforts</i>

884
00:32:33,944 --> 00:32:36,747
<i>gives me so much joy.</i>

885
00:32:36,813 --> 00:32:39,483
That alone makes
everything worthwhile for me.

886
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:40,884
I felt so happy.

887
00:32:41,785 --> 00:32:43,120
I was over the moon about it.

888
00:32:43,186 --> 00:32:44,621
SHE WAS HAPPY TO SEE DANIEL HAPPY

889
00:32:44,855 --> 00:32:46,690
I don't know what to say.
But above all else

890
00:32:46,757 --> 00:32:48,959
I know I'll remember
my birthday this year

891
00:32:49,026 --> 00:32:50,827
for a long time.

892
00:32:50,894 --> 00:32:51,962
FROM LONESOME BIRTHDAYS

893
00:32:52,029 --> 00:32:56,166
TO AN UNFORGETTABLE ONE
THANKS TO HIS FRIEND'S CARE

894
00:32:56,233 --> 00:32:58,402
Let's give Da-hee a big hand
for her touching present.

895
00:32:59,002 --> 00:33:00,604
Thank you, Da-hee.

896
00:33:01,772 --> 00:33:03,140
Wear them well, okay?

897
00:33:03,540 --> 00:33:05,409
- What?
- Wear the shoes well.

898
00:33:06,276 --> 00:33:07,411
I sure will.

899
00:33:07,844 --> 00:33:09,613
- Put those slippers back on.
- Yes, ma'am.

900
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:11,515
Should I go get changed?

901
00:33:11,582 --> 00:33:12,950
Yes, we don't want it wrinkled.

902
00:33:13,016 --> 00:33:14,284
- You need that tomorrow.
- Okay.

903
00:33:14,351 --> 00:33:15,786
- Hurry.
- All right.

904
00:33:16,253 --> 00:33:17,254
- Make it quick
- Sure.

905
00:33:17,321 --> 00:33:18,355
if you don't want an earful.

906
00:33:18,889 --> 00:33:21,491
DA-HEE'S THREAT OF A SCOLDING
DOESN'T AFFECT HIS ENTHUSIASM

907
00:33:21,692 --> 00:33:23,360
It's so nice to see him excited.

908
00:33:24,962 --> 00:33:27,864
NO ONE WILL MISTAKE
THE CHEERFUL ENERGY IN HIS STEPS

909
00:33:29,566 --> 00:33:31,702
GRINNING WIDELY

910
00:33:32,269 --> 00:33:34,037
What a fantastic suit.

911
00:33:35,539 --> 00:33:37,441
HE CLEARLY LIKES IT SO MUCH

912
00:33:38,609 --> 00:33:40,611
TOSS

913
00:33:40,677 --> 00:33:44,681
HE'S MAKING A SPECIAL EFFORT
TO HANG HIS CLOTHES

914
00:33:45,449 --> 00:33:48,652
A PRECIOUS SET OF SUIT AND SHOES
HE FINALLY GOT TO OWN AFTER 40 YEARS

915
00:33:49,386 --> 00:33:52,089
- Let's say we're going to bed
- Okay.

916
00:33:52,155 --> 00:33:53,156
and head to our rooms.

917
00:33:53,223 --> 00:33:54,992
We can gather again around 11:30 p.m.

918
00:33:55,592 --> 00:33:56,627
Okay.

919
00:33:56,693 --> 00:33:57,928
We'll celebrate his birthday then.

920
00:33:57,995 --> 00:33:59,162
WAS THIS ABOUT HIS BIRTHDAY PARTY?

921
00:33:59,229 --> 00:34:00,230
I like the idea.

922
00:34:01,064 --> 00:34:02,599
It's so strange

923
00:34:02,666 --> 00:34:04,935
how everyone thinks
of a surprise event for birthdays.

924
00:34:06,269 --> 00:34:08,071
Keep an eye on him, okay?

925
00:34:08,138 --> 00:34:09,206
PLANNING A SURPRISE FOR DANIEL

926
00:34:09,272 --> 00:34:10,607
He won't stick around here, will he?

927
00:34:10,674 --> 00:34:11,675
He won't.

928
00:34:11,742 --> 00:34:14,411
- We can suggest a lights-out.
- He might not go to bed.

929
00:34:14,611 --> 00:34:16,613
- Keep a close eye on him.
- Yeah.

930
00:34:16,680 --> 00:34:18,081
We can wake him up
if he falls asleep.

931
00:34:18,148 --> 00:34:19,149
HE CARES LITTLE FOR BIRTHDAYS

932
00:34:19,816 --> 00:34:23,587
IT HAS BEEN ALMOST 20 YEARS
HE CELEBRATED HIS BIRTHDAY

933
00:34:23,654 --> 00:34:26,623
Let's make it a cute surprise
so it won't come as too big a shock.

934
00:34:26,690 --> 00:34:28,659
LIKE HIS FATHER'S MOCHA MOUSSE CAKE
ABOUT 30 YEARS AGO

935
00:34:28,725 --> 00:34:29,760
You don't like the idea?

936
00:34:29,826 --> 00:34:31,194
When he comes downstairs

937
00:34:31,261 --> 00:34:32,529
we can all go, "Good work today."

938
00:34:32,596 --> 00:34:34,064
- Let's try a rehearsal.
- "Good night."

939
00:34:34,531 --> 00:34:35,632
HOW WILL THEIR SURPRISE EVENT GO?

940
00:34:35,699 --> 00:34:36,733
"Let's go to bed now."

941
00:34:37,668 --> 00:34:39,503
- When do we gather again?
- At 11:40 p.m.

942
00:34:39,970 --> 00:34:40,971
At 11:40 p.m?

943
00:34:41,038 --> 00:34:42,072
Okay.

944
00:34:43,140 --> 00:34:45,208
THE MAN OF THE DAY COMES DOWNSTAIRS

945
00:34:45,275 --> 00:34:46,343
Gugi-dong.

946
00:34:47,277 --> 00:34:48,278
It's time to go to bed.

947
00:34:48,345 --> 00:34:49,680
AT SOUNDS OF DANIEL'S FOOTSTEPS

948
00:34:49,746 --> 00:34:51,848
EVERYONE JUMPS TO ACTION AS PLANNED

949
00:34:52,616 --> 00:34:53,617
What time is it now?

950
00:34:53,684 --> 00:34:55,152
Isn't it about time we went to bed?

951
00:34:55,218 --> 00:34:57,754
- I should turn in early tonight.
- Let's go to bed.

952
00:34:57,821 --> 00:34:59,890
- Good night.
- Sleep tight.

953
00:34:59,956 --> 00:35:02,092
AND SO, THE ACTORS BEGIN
THEIR BIT ABOUT GOING TO BED EARLY

954
00:35:02,626 --> 00:35:04,928
IS EVERYONE GOING TO BED?

955
00:35:04,995 --> 00:35:06,563
- Good night.
- Good night.

956
00:35:06,630 --> 00:35:09,132
DANIEL IS DRIVEN INTO GOING UPSTAIRS

957
00:35:09,833 --> 00:35:13,136
SOMEWHAT DISSATISFIED

958
00:35:14,137 --> 00:35:15,806
Daniel seemed rather upset.

959
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:17,941
HOW CUTE, RIGHT?

960
00:35:18,008 --> 00:35:19,009
I don't know about that.

961
00:35:21,011 --> 00:35:22,312
My back hurts.

962
00:35:22,379 --> 00:35:24,181
- Good night, Keun-suk.
- Rest up, guys.

963
00:35:24,247 --> 00:35:25,248
Sleep tight.

964
00:35:25,582 --> 00:35:27,317
HEAVY STEPS

965
00:35:28,585 --> 00:35:31,388
APPROACHES CAUTIOUSLY

966
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:32,689
Good night, Daniel.

967
00:35:33,023 --> 00:35:34,157
Sure, sleep tight.

968
00:35:34,224 --> 00:35:35,992
Are you going to go to bed
right away? I'm not.

969
00:35:36,059 --> 00:35:37,060
Still, rest well.

970
00:35:37,127 --> 00:35:38,462
Good night for now.

971
00:35:38,528 --> 00:35:39,529
Okay.

972
00:35:39,596 --> 00:35:41,298
HE CLEARLY SOUNDS DISAPPOINTED

973
00:35:42,899 --> 00:35:44,034
SIGHS

974
00:35:44,768 --> 00:35:48,205
JAE-HYEON MANAGED TO RETURN
TO HIS ROOM SUCCESSFULLY

975
00:35:50,207 --> 00:35:51,975
LET ME THINK...

976
00:35:52,042 --> 00:35:53,043
It's 11:20 p.m.

977
00:35:53,410 --> 00:35:55,746
HOW DO I LEAVE THIS ROOM?

978
00:35:56,079 --> 00:35:57,914
Should we head out? It's 11:41 p.m.

979
00:35:57,981 --> 00:35:59,049
Let's keep it down.

980
00:35:59,116 --> 00:36:00,350
20 MINUTES BEFORE DANIEL TURNS FORTY

981
00:36:00,417 --> 00:36:03,453
THEY SNEAK OUTSIDE
AT THE PROMISED TIME

982
00:36:04,187 --> 00:36:07,190
BUT NO ONE IS IN THE LIVING ROOM

983
00:36:07,924 --> 00:36:09,659
I hope they haven't fallen asleep.

984
00:36:10,894 --> 00:36:14,364
HURRYING TO SET UP THE CAKE
THEY ORDERED IN SECRET

985
00:36:14,931 --> 00:36:16,700
IS IT SAFE TO GO OUT?

986
00:36:17,134 --> 00:36:18,435
Let's set up the candles.

987
00:36:20,137 --> 00:36:21,138
Okay.

988
00:36:21,772 --> 00:36:23,874
- What time is it?
- It's 11:45 p.m.

989
00:36:24,274 --> 00:36:26,343
IT'S TIME THEY GATHERED

990
00:36:26,977 --> 00:36:29,746
BUT JAE-HYEON IS
STILL STUCK IN HIS ROOM

991
00:36:31,014 --> 00:36:34,951
DANIEL GOES OUT TO THE TERRACE
NOT WANTING TO GO TO BED SO EARLY

992
00:36:35,652 --> 00:36:36,953
No, I spend the day alone.

993
00:36:37,020 --> 00:36:39,856
IS HE PLANNING TO SPEND
HIS 40TH BIRTHDAY ALONE AS WELL?

994
00:36:40,690 --> 00:36:42,726
DID DANIEL LEAVE HIS ROOM?

995
00:36:42,793 --> 00:36:44,728
KNOCKS

996
00:36:45,228 --> 00:36:47,831
AFTER CHECKING
THAT DANIEL IS NOT IN HIS ROOM

997
00:36:48,465 --> 00:36:50,433
SUCCESSFULLY ESCAPES HIS ROOM

998
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:53,069
CONFIRMS THAT DANIEL IS
ON THE TERRACE

999
00:36:53,503 --> 00:36:55,472
He's checking his phone
out on the terrace.

1000
00:36:55,539 --> 00:36:56,540
- Who?
- Daniel.

1001
00:36:56,606 --> 00:36:57,607
- Daniel?
- Daniel.

1002
00:36:57,974 --> 00:37:01,344
AP FINALLY COMES DOWNSTAIRS
AFTER WAITING OUT OF CAUTION

1003
00:37:01,411 --> 00:37:02,512
I have a good idea.

1004
00:37:02,579 --> 00:37:04,181
Let's all go up to my room.

1005
00:37:04,247 --> 00:37:05,682
His room is right next to mine.

1006
00:37:06,383 --> 00:37:08,985
Hey, that's right. I like the idea
of waiting in his room.

1007
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,922
Apparently, Daniel's preoccupied
with something out on the terrace.

1008
00:37:11,988 --> 00:37:13,990
Can someone go to him?

1009
00:37:14,057 --> 00:37:15,892
- Keep him busy.
- We can't have him come to us.

1010
00:37:16,092 --> 00:37:17,093
I'll go talk to him.

1011
00:37:17,160 --> 00:37:18,695
Okay, then. Let's do that.

1012
00:37:19,062 --> 00:37:22,499
EVERYONE WILL GO TO JAE-HYEON'S ROOM
WHILE KEUN-SUK DISTRACTS DANIEL

1013
00:37:22,699 --> 00:37:24,401
11 MINUTES BEFORE DANIEL TURNS FORTY

1014
00:37:24,467 --> 00:37:25,802
- Daniel.
- Yes?

1015
00:37:26,703 --> 00:37:29,306
CHECKS THAT KEUN-SUK
HAS JOINED DANIEL

1016
00:37:29,906 --> 00:37:32,142
This is it. Come upstairs slowly.

1017
00:37:32,209 --> 00:37:34,511
- We're coming.
- Come on. Be careful.

1018
00:37:35,078 --> 00:37:36,546
Slowly. He can't see here.

1019
00:37:36,780 --> 00:37:38,548
It's been a pretty rough day for me.

1020
00:37:38,615 --> 00:37:40,717
KEUN-SUK SHARES HIS FAKE CONCERNS
TO DISTRACT DANIEL

1021
00:37:40,784 --> 00:37:41,785
Go.

1022
00:37:41,852 --> 00:37:42,953
9 MINUTES BEFORE DANIEL TURNS FORTY

1023
00:37:43,019 --> 00:37:44,754
Go to the bathroom.

1024
00:37:44,821 --> 00:37:45,956
WE CAN'T LET DANIEL TURN FORTY ALONE

1025
00:37:46,022 --> 00:37:47,724
Go to the bathroom.

1026
00:37:47,791 --> 00:37:50,227
JAE-HYEON'S ROOM, DANIEL'S ROOM
BATHROOM

1027
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:52,162
THE GIRLS ENTER JAE-HYEON'S ROOM

1028
00:37:52,229 --> 00:37:54,231
- What a curious layout.
- They share this bathroom.

1029
00:37:54,297 --> 00:37:56,299
- This is Jae-hyeon's room?
- Yes, that's Daniel's room.

1030
00:37:56,366 --> 00:37:57,701
It's tiny.

1031
00:37:57,767 --> 00:37:58,869
- My gosh.
- Let's shut the door.

1032
00:37:59,269 --> 00:38:00,370
AN UNEXPECTED SURPRISE

1033
00:38:00,437 --> 00:38:01,605
- That's Daniel's room.
- Close it.

1034
00:38:02,572 --> 00:38:03,607
7 MINUTES BEFORE DANIEL TURNS FORTY

1035
00:38:03,673 --> 00:38:08,311
ALL THEY NEED IS THE MAN OF THE DAY

1036
00:38:12,249 --> 00:38:16,519
AHN-GEL IS A TERRIBLE LIAR
BUT HE MUST PLAY THE KEY ROLE TONIGHT

1037
00:38:17,787 --> 00:38:20,891
WHAT IS THE SOLUTION HE FOUND
AFTER MUCH DELIBERATION?

1038
00:38:21,892 --> 00:38:24,294
Can I borrow something to wear
tomorrow, Keun-suk?

1039
00:38:24,361 --> 00:38:25,962
- What?
- Remember that thing you showed me?

1040
00:38:26,029 --> 00:38:28,665
A MASTERPIECE LIE FOOLING
HIS OWN CONSPIRATOR

1041
00:38:28,732 --> 00:38:30,834
- Oh, I get it.
- The one from earlier in the day.

1042
00:38:31,468 --> 00:38:33,470
- Not that orange one.
- Right.

1043
00:38:34,004 --> 00:38:35,305
Was it suede?

1044
00:38:35,772 --> 00:38:37,841
What's the material called again?
It was giving Chanel.

1045
00:38:38,541 --> 00:38:41,244
3 MINUTES BEFORE DANIEL TURNS FORTY

1046
00:38:41,878 --> 00:38:44,047
Put this on and ask for his opinion.

1047
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:45,782
ON THE SAME WAVELENGTH

1048
00:38:45,849 --> 00:38:47,150
Okay, let's go.

1049
00:38:47,484 --> 00:38:49,252
- How do I look?
- What do you think?

1050
00:38:49,319 --> 00:38:50,620
TWO GROWN MEN TRYING HARD
FOR A SURPRISE PARTY

1051
00:38:50,687 --> 00:38:52,088
- For when?
- Tomorrow.

1052
00:38:52,856 --> 00:38:53,857
What about the top?

1053
00:38:53,924 --> 00:38:56,459
I'll find something
in a matching color.

1054
00:38:57,193 --> 00:38:59,262
Can I pair this jacket
with those black glasses of yours?

1055
00:39:00,096 --> 00:39:01,097
How many pairs do you own?

1056
00:39:01,164 --> 00:39:02,599
- I have loads.
- I think I saw quite a few.

1057
00:39:02,666 --> 00:39:04,367
- Can I go check them out?
- Sure, go ahead.

1058
00:39:04,434 --> 00:39:06,303
- Come with me.
- You should be there.

1059
00:39:06,736 --> 00:39:07,837
Take whatever you want.

1060
00:39:07,904 --> 00:39:09,406
Oh, come on. It's not the same.

1061
00:39:09,472 --> 00:39:11,174
I should try them on with you.

1062
00:39:13,543 --> 00:39:15,145
- Come on, it's cold here.
- Lend him a pair.

1063
00:39:15,211 --> 00:39:16,746
- All right.
- It's cold out here.

1064
00:39:16,813 --> 00:39:18,114
HE GOT UP TO HIS FEET!

1065
00:39:18,181 --> 00:39:19,282
I just wanted you to look

1066
00:39:19,950 --> 00:39:21,284
- without me hovering.
- It's cold.

1067
00:39:21,518 --> 00:39:23,954
Okay, I'll show them to you.

1068
00:39:24,020 --> 00:39:25,188
COUGHS AS A SIGNAL

1069
00:39:25,255 --> 00:39:26,256
COUGHS

1070
00:39:26,423 --> 00:39:27,624
He coughed twice.

1071
00:39:27,691 --> 00:39:28,692
THEY'RE COMING

1072
00:39:28,925 --> 00:39:30,727
Okay, that seems good.

1073
00:39:30,794 --> 00:39:32,896
EVERYTHING IS SET
FOR DANIEL'S 40TH BIRTHDAY PARTY

1074
00:39:33,763 --> 00:39:34,831
It's not cold.

1075
00:39:34,898 --> 00:39:36,433
HE DOESN'T SUSPECT A THING

1076
00:39:36,499 --> 00:39:38,134
It's not cold at all.

1077
00:39:38,201 --> 00:39:39,502
SNEAKS A LOOK

1078
00:39:40,003 --> 00:39:42,339
- My glasses...
- Your room's pretty neat.

1079
00:39:43,273 --> 00:39:46,476
THE FIRST BIRTHDAY PARTY
IN ABOUT 20 YEARS

1080
00:39:46,543 --> 00:39:49,579
HOW WILL HE REACT TO THIS SURPRISE?

1081
00:39:49,646 --> 00:39:51,614
THIS IS IT!

1082
00:39:55,618 --> 00:39:56,953
- Where is this from?
- What on earth?

1083
00:39:57,020 --> 00:40:00,757
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>

1084
00:40:00,824 --> 00:40:02,525
REALLY TURNING FORTY

1085
00:40:02,592 --> 00:40:05,462
REALLY STARTLED

1086
00:40:06,029 --> 00:40:08,598
HE'S JAW LITERALLY DROPPED
FROM SURPRISE

1087
00:40:08,665 --> 00:40:13,003
<i>- Dear Daniel Henney</i>
- Did someone say Daniel Henney?

1088
00:40:13,069 --> 00:40:16,973
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>
<i>- Happy birthday to you</i>

1089
00:40:18,241 --> 00:40:19,509
Blow out the candles.

1090
00:40:19,576 --> 00:40:21,911
- You should make a wish.
- What's all this?

1091
00:40:21,978 --> 00:40:23,146
- Make a wish first.
- Okay.

1092
00:40:23,213 --> 00:40:24,547
Don't forget your wish.

1093
00:40:26,282 --> 00:40:27,450
A BIRTHDAY WISH AFTER A LONG TIME

1094
00:40:27,517 --> 00:40:28,752
I hope

1095
00:40:29,019 --> 00:40:33,356
we can all enjoy our time shooting
<i>Six Singles Under One Roof.</i>

1096
00:40:33,423 --> 00:40:35,925
I hope we can stay in touch
and meet regularly afterward.

1097
00:40:35,992 --> 00:40:37,260
Thank you so much, guys.

1098
00:40:37,327 --> 00:40:38,661
- Take them all out.
- Congrats.

1099
00:40:38,728 --> 00:40:40,196
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

1100
00:40:41,131 --> 00:40:42,232
- Congrats.
- Happy birthday.

1101
00:40:42,298 --> 00:40:43,433
Thank you.

1102
00:40:43,500 --> 00:40:44,634
THANK YOU

1103
00:40:44,701 --> 00:40:49,906
FOR SPENDING MY BIRTHDAY WITH ME

1104
00:40:50,473 --> 00:40:51,741
THE SURPRISE EVENT ENDED IN A SUCCESS

1105
00:40:51,808 --> 00:40:53,043
What is all this, though?

1106
00:40:53,610 --> 00:40:54,744
Did you catch on to us or what?

1107
00:40:54,811 --> 00:40:55,879
Not at all. I had no idea.

1108
00:40:55,945 --> 00:40:57,547
- Really?
- Did you have to stay outside?

1109
00:40:57,614 --> 00:40:58,648
Well...

1110
00:40:59,282 --> 00:41:00,817
- You took so long.
- You all went to bed.

1111
00:41:01,718 --> 00:41:02,952
So I thought that was that.

1112
00:41:03,019 --> 00:41:05,622
Didn't we upset you
when we all left at 11:30 p.m.?

1113
00:41:05,688 --> 00:41:06,923
Not at all.

1114
00:41:06,990 --> 00:41:09,426
I haven't celebrated
my birthday for so long.

1115
00:41:09,492 --> 00:41:10,927
- I knew it.
- I never expected this.

1116
00:41:10,994 --> 00:41:12,028
Happy birthday.

1117
00:41:12,095 --> 00:41:13,163
- Congrats.
- Happy birthday.

1118
00:41:13,229 --> 00:41:15,365
- Congrats!
- Thank you. You guys rock.

1119
00:41:15,432 --> 00:41:17,333
- Let's eat this tomorrow.
- Let's do that.

1120
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:19,402
We can enjoy it after a meal.

1121
00:41:20,203 --> 00:41:21,838
- Okay.
- We timed it just right.

1122
00:41:21,905 --> 00:41:23,073
- Stop filming.
- Wait.

1123
00:41:23,139 --> 00:41:25,442
- What's going on?
- Come on, don't put on a show.

1124
00:41:25,508 --> 00:41:26,776
No way. You can't be crying.

1125
00:41:26,843 --> 00:41:28,545
Don't cry, you dummy!

1126
00:41:28,611 --> 00:41:30,380
- Are you crying for real?
- No, I'm not.

1127
00:41:30,447 --> 00:41:31,781
I was just so startled

1128
00:41:31,848 --> 00:41:33,850
that I let the smoke
get into my eyes.

1129
00:41:34,284 --> 00:41:36,186
- You're crying.
- I'm not.

1130
00:41:36,986 --> 00:41:38,388
What a crybaby.

1131
00:41:38,455 --> 00:41:40,256
Go ahead and tell your family

1132
00:41:40,323 --> 00:41:42,425
- that you're so loved here.
- I'll have to do that.

1133
00:41:42,492 --> 00:41:43,760
Share this with your father.

1134
00:41:43,827 --> 00:41:46,696
My dad will be delighted
when he watches this episode.

1135
00:41:46,763 --> 00:41:48,965
My dear old widower dad.

1136
00:41:51,935 --> 00:41:53,603
- Call him and tell him you love him.
- Okay.

1137
00:41:53,670 --> 00:41:55,105
It's midnight,
the time you were born.

1138
00:41:55,171 --> 00:41:56,506
- It's 12 a.m. sharp.
- Right.

1139
00:41:56,573 --> 00:41:58,775
It's nice to live together.
We get to celebrate it together.

1140
00:41:58,842 --> 00:42:00,777
- It's lovely.
- Yes, we really feel good.

1141
00:42:00,844 --> 00:42:02,011
Turns out I was an idiot.

1142
00:42:02,812 --> 00:42:04,547
Seriously, I'm so touched.

1143
00:42:04,614 --> 00:42:07,951
I honestly thought
you were all too tired.

1144
00:42:08,017 --> 00:42:09,352
- We are tired.
- Right?

1145
00:42:09,419 --> 00:42:10,820
- True that.
- Speaking of

1146
00:42:10,887 --> 00:42:11,988
- we'll get going.
- Okay.

1147
00:42:13,990 --> 00:42:15,525
- Anyhow, Daniel.
- It was so nice.

1148
00:42:15,592 --> 00:42:17,227
- Thank you so much.
- See you tomorrow.

1149
00:42:17,293 --> 00:42:18,628
- Thanks, guys.
- See you in the morning.

1150
00:42:18,695 --> 00:42:19,896
Good night.

1151
00:42:19,963 --> 00:42:21,764
- Sleep tight.
- We pulled it off, guys.

1152
00:42:21,831 --> 00:42:23,066
Pretty heartwarming, right?

1153
00:42:23,133 --> 00:42:24,934
- You can say that again.
- I'm so proud of ourselves.

1154
00:42:25,401 --> 00:42:27,203
Look at the picture.

1155
00:42:27,270 --> 00:42:28,271
What do you think?

1156
00:42:29,139 --> 00:42:30,140
It's so cute.

1157
00:42:30,206 --> 00:42:32,142
- Can I keep it?
- Of course.

1158
00:42:32,575 --> 00:42:33,977
- It's yours.
- For sure.

1159
00:42:34,410 --> 00:42:35,545
Here's the photo I took.

1160
00:42:35,612 --> 00:42:37,180
I'M SO TOUCHED

1161
00:42:38,081 --> 00:42:40,316
PHOTOS OF THE SAME MOMENT

1162
00:42:40,383 --> 00:42:41,518
Can I use that as my profile picture?

1163
00:42:41,584 --> 00:42:43,186
CARRYING DIFFERENT EMOTIONS

1164
00:42:44,187 --> 00:42:46,189
I honestly didn't see this coming.
Hey, what's that?

1165
00:42:47,590 --> 00:42:48,825
Good work, Keun-suk.

1166
00:42:48,892 --> 00:42:50,326
Hey, I'm glad we did this.

1167
00:42:50,393 --> 00:42:52,629
- Daniel got really misty-eyed.
- I know.

1168
00:42:52,695 --> 00:42:55,698
- Was he touched?
- Is this his first surprise party?

1169
00:42:56,466 --> 00:43:00,170
DANIEL IS LEFT ALONE
FOR A SHORT WHILE

1170
00:43:01,171 --> 00:43:04,274
HE KEEPS LOOKING AT THE PHOTO

1171
00:43:05,708 --> 00:43:08,878
A PRECIOUS SECOND MEMORY

1172
00:43:08,945 --> 00:43:11,981
OF A BIRTHDAY WITH HIS FAM

1173
00:43:12,182 --> 00:43:13,583
Is this the first surprise

1174
00:43:13,650 --> 00:43:14,684
- in a while?
- I'm so touched.

1175
00:43:14,984 --> 00:43:15,985
- Is that it?
- Yeah.

1176
00:43:16,052 --> 00:43:17,353
- Why are you crying?
- Oh, come on.

1177
00:43:17,420 --> 00:43:18,821
What's going on?

1178
00:43:18,888 --> 00:43:20,056
- Don't cry.
- What's with you?

1179
00:43:21,090 --> 00:43:22,292
I'm so touched.

1180
00:43:22,759 --> 00:43:24,360
- This is it.
- It's our shot.

1181
00:43:24,427 --> 00:43:25,962
- Look here, Daniel.
- Whatever for?

1182
00:43:26,029 --> 00:43:27,931
- Come on, look here.
- Cut it out.

1183
00:43:29,699 --> 00:43:31,434
The thought didn't even occur to me.

1184
00:43:31,501 --> 00:43:33,002
Why didn't I think of this?

1185
00:43:33,570 --> 00:43:35,205
- Good night.
- He's crying, guys.

1186
00:43:35,271 --> 00:43:36,306
- He's started crying.
- No.

1187
00:43:36,372 --> 00:43:38,074
- Really?
- Not at all.

1188
00:43:38,141 --> 00:43:39,642
- He's crying for real.
- No, I'm not.

1189
00:43:40,643 --> 00:43:42,045
The photo came out really well.

1190
00:43:42,779 --> 00:43:44,647
- What's going on?
- Don't cry!

1191
00:43:44,714 --> 00:43:46,449
- Would you look at that?
- What's up with you?

1192
00:43:46,516 --> 00:43:48,885
- What's going on?
- Come on, Daniel.

1193
00:43:48,952 --> 00:43:49,953
EVERYONE TEARS UP

1194
00:43:50,019 --> 00:43:51,454
You guys caught a beautiful scene.

1195
00:43:51,521 --> 00:43:52,822
- It's a good one.
- Can I take a look?

1196
00:43:52,889 --> 00:43:54,190
Now, we're the startled ones.

1197
00:43:54,257 --> 00:43:56,359
So cute, right?
It's a wonderful photo.

1198
00:43:56,426 --> 00:43:59,095
HE HAS LONG THOUGHT
BIRTHDAYS WERE NOTHING SPECIAL

1199
00:43:59,162 --> 00:44:00,597
I'm so glad we prepared this.

1200
00:44:00,663 --> 00:44:03,132
- Totally.
- My heart feels full somehow.

1201
00:44:03,199 --> 00:44:05,235
We meant to please you
with the surprise event, but...

1202
00:44:05,301 --> 00:44:07,770
- We're unexpectedly moved.
- Yes, we feel rewarded somehow.

1203
00:44:08,504 --> 00:44:09,706
All of a sudden...

1204
00:44:09,772 --> 00:44:14,744
SOMETIMES, LITTLE EXCHANGES
CAN MEAN THE WORLD TO YOU

1205
00:44:14,811 --> 00:44:16,579
Make sure to remember this, Daniel.

1206
00:44:16,646 --> 00:44:18,448
- Your day has just begun.
- That's right.

1207
00:44:18,514 --> 00:44:19,682
- So true.
- You're right.

1208
00:44:19,749 --> 00:44:21,918
You never know what kind of surprises
might be waiting for you.

1209
00:44:22,285 --> 00:44:23,386
Your day is just beginning.

1210
00:44:23,453 --> 00:44:24,854
Emotional stuff always leaves me

1211
00:44:24,921 --> 00:44:26,122
stumbling over words.

1212
00:44:26,689 --> 00:44:27,824
I get a T in MBTI.

1213
00:44:28,258 --> 00:44:29,459
- What's going on?
- What's with him?

1214
00:44:30,059 --> 00:44:32,095
WHILE TRYING TO LEAN
ON THE COUCH'S BACKREST

1215
00:44:33,429 --> 00:44:35,531
HE STUMBLES AND FALLS TO THE FLOOR

1216
00:44:36,232 --> 00:44:37,233
What's with you?

1217
00:44:38,067 --> 00:44:39,569
- That was a silly thing to do.
- What was that?

1218
00:44:39,636 --> 00:44:40,970
- He's a dummy.
- What happened?

1219
00:44:41,037 --> 00:44:42,272
- What did he do?
- He's just being silly.

1220
00:44:42,338 --> 00:44:45,108
He rolled and landed
on the floor like some hero.

1221
00:44:45,441 --> 00:44:47,043
- Let's go to bed now.
- Okay.

1222
00:44:47,110 --> 00:44:48,811
- Good night.
- Good night.

1223
00:44:48,878 --> 00:44:50,980
- Sleep tight!
- Thank you so much.

1224
00:44:52,682 --> 00:44:58,721
EVERYONE ELSE HAS GONE TO BED

1225
00:44:59,656 --> 00:45:04,160
BUT SLEEP WON'T COME EASY TO DANIEL

1226
00:45:04,227 --> 00:45:07,964
ESPECIALLY TONIGHT

1227
00:45:15,138 --> 00:45:21,744
A MYRIAD OF EMOTIONS WASHES OVER HIM

1228
00:45:25,848 --> 00:45:28,584
<i>It's been forever</i>
<i>since I last celebrated my birthday.</i>

1229
00:45:30,386 --> 00:45:33,923
The fact that my birthday came

1230
00:45:34,290 --> 00:45:39,128
while I was staying here in Gugi-dong
