1522
00:56:42,719 --> 00:56:44,754
WHAT ARE DA-HEE AND DO-YEON DOING?

1523
00:56:44,821 --> 00:56:47,157
It feels like my body
is about to shatter into pieces.

1524
00:56:48,058 --> 00:56:49,559
Are you feverish? I hope not.

1525
00:56:49,626 --> 00:56:53,063
I think all the dancing yesterday

1526
00:56:53,129 --> 00:56:54,798
messed up my muscles.

1527
00:56:55,799 --> 00:56:58,334
THE MUSCLE ACHES MAKE THEM
PAINFULLY AWARE OF THEIR AGE

1528
00:56:58,902 --> 00:57:00,270
Look who's up.

1529
00:57:00,336 --> 00:57:01,404
You're here. Did you sleep well?

1530
00:57:02,038 --> 00:57:03,373
- How are you feeling?
- My gosh.

1531
00:57:03,440 --> 00:57:04,474
Yes.

1532
00:57:04,541 --> 00:57:05,642
Hey.

1533
00:57:07,544 --> 00:57:08,912
Hey.

1534
00:57:08,978 --> 00:57:10,780
- Check this out, Do-yeon.
- My gosh. I feel so bad...

1535
00:57:10,847 --> 00:57:12,916
Don't you feel like trying this
before going back to bed?

1536
00:57:13,750 --> 00:57:16,386
- We've got braised short ribs.
- Hey, this looks like a food model.

1537
00:57:16,453 --> 00:57:17,721
Come have breakfast.

1538
00:57:17,787 --> 00:57:19,355
<i>Wow, what's up</i>
<i>with the braised short ribs?</i>

1539
00:57:19,422 --> 00:57:20,957
<i>It looks amazing.</i>

1540
00:57:21,024 --> 00:57:22,058
<i>Look at all the side dishes.</i>

1541
00:57:22,125 --> 00:57:23,760
<i>It's giving a proper feast</i>
<i>for an elder.</i>

1542
00:57:23,827 --> 00:57:24,828
<i>Gosh.</i>

1543
00:57:24,894 --> 00:57:26,196
<i>Wow! A birthday feast!</i>

1544
00:57:26,896 --> 00:57:29,132
NONE OF THEM COULD'VE DREAMED OF THIS
WHILE LIVING ALONE

1545
00:57:29,199 --> 00:57:30,900
What is all this?

1546
00:57:30,967 --> 00:57:33,103
- What is all this?
- Your birthday breakfast, of course.

1547
00:57:33,169 --> 00:57:34,337
- Congrats.
- My goodness.

1548
00:57:34,604 --> 00:57:36,106
One, two, three.

1549
00:57:36,639 --> 00:57:38,808
<i>- Happy birthday!</i>
<i>- Thanks.</i>

1550
00:57:38,875 --> 00:57:40,009
<i>Thanks, guys.</i>

1551
00:57:41,010 --> 00:57:42,378
Is it good?

1552
00:57:42,445 --> 00:57:43,913
THE MAN OF THE DAY
TRIES THE WARM SOUP FIRST

1553
00:57:43,980 --> 00:57:46,216
Your last touch made
all the difference, Soo-jin.

1554
00:57:46,282 --> 00:57:47,383
Guys!

1555
00:57:47,450 --> 00:57:49,285
- This is great.
- You think so?

1556
00:57:49,886 --> 00:57:50,887
- Really?
- It's perfect.

1557
00:57:50,954 --> 00:57:52,455
- I mean it.
- It's great.

1558
00:57:53,423 --> 00:57:55,925
- It's for Daniel's birthday.
- It's amazing.

1559
00:57:56,760 --> 00:57:57,927
- It's a killer, right?
- Yeah.

1560
00:57:57,994 --> 00:57:59,262
You got that right.

1561
00:57:59,729 --> 00:58:01,397
EXCITED LIKE A LITTLE KID

1562
00:58:01,464 --> 00:58:03,133
Gosh, Soo-jin. This is incredible.

1563
00:58:03,199 --> 00:58:04,567
Oh, man. It's just...

1564
00:58:04,634 --> 00:58:06,836
A 40-YEAR-OLD CHILD
MAKING ALL THE EFFORTS WORTHWHILE

1565
00:58:07,337 --> 00:58:09,239
RUSHES TO TAKE A BIG BITE

1566
00:58:09,539 --> 00:58:11,641
HAVE SOME MORE

1567
00:58:13,009 --> 00:58:14,310
The seaweed soup is to die for.

1568
00:58:14,778 --> 00:58:16,112
Everything tastes so good to me.

1569
00:58:16,179 --> 00:58:17,680
THANK GOODNESS
HE'S ENJOYING ALL THE FOOD

1570
00:58:17,747 --> 00:58:19,849
What a joy you've been bringing me
since last night.

1571
00:58:20,817 --> 00:58:21,985
I can't be sure.

1572
00:58:22,051 --> 00:58:23,119
Who is that supposed to be?

1573
00:58:26,923 --> 00:58:27,924
- What's wrong?
- What's up?

1574
00:58:28,925 --> 00:58:30,360
- Did you try the soup?
- Maybe <i>japchae?</i>

1575
00:58:30,426 --> 00:58:31,728
Who made <i>japchae?</i>

1576
00:58:31,795 --> 00:58:33,263
- We got that from a store.
- I see.

1577
00:58:33,329 --> 00:58:35,532
- Are you trolling us or what?
- The owner did a fine job.

1578
00:58:35,598 --> 00:58:36,633
Gosh.

1579
00:58:36,966 --> 00:58:38,134
I SEE

1580
00:58:38,201 --> 00:58:39,369
It's great.

1581
00:58:39,903 --> 00:58:42,205
I GUESS WE'RE GOOD
AS LONG AS YOU ENJOY EVERYTHING

1582
00:58:42,539 --> 00:58:44,040
I know this is a selfish thing to say

1583
00:58:44,107 --> 00:58:46,376
but I loved waking up
to the smell of food.

1584
00:58:46,910 --> 00:58:49,045
- The delicious smell filled my room.
- You know...

1585
00:58:49,112 --> 00:58:51,314
UPSIDE OF LIVING TOGETHER
WAKING UP TO AN AMAZING AROMA

1586
00:58:51,381 --> 00:58:53,883
You know, all the stress melts away
when you see people enjoy your food.

1587
00:58:53,950 --> 00:58:54,951
That's so true.

1588
00:58:55,451 --> 00:58:56,486
It's so satisfying.

1589
00:58:57,921 --> 00:58:59,355
We all had a feast
thanks to your birthday.

1590
00:58:59,422 --> 00:59:01,191
I know. Who'd have thought?

1591
00:59:03,193 --> 00:59:04,961
Did any of you
have a good dream last night?

1592
00:59:05,028 --> 00:59:06,329
You have a group date today.

1593
00:59:07,130 --> 00:59:08,631
I had a dreamless night.

1594
00:59:09,399 --> 00:59:11,034
What do I do with the date, though?

1595
00:59:11,401 --> 00:59:12,735
What if

1596
00:59:13,670 --> 00:59:16,472
