1599
00:59:20,076 --> 00:59:22,245
- So the woman...
- Do you want to be a heartbreaker?

1600
00:59:22,312 --> 00:59:24,247
So in this scenario,
she seems interested in you

1601
00:59:24,314 --> 00:59:25,882
- but you don't feel the same way?
- Yeah.

1602
00:59:25,949 --> 00:59:27,217
That can happen, right?

1603
00:59:27,283 --> 00:59:28,351
- Sure.
- Of course.

1604
00:59:28,418 --> 00:59:29,719
That's the scenario

1605
00:59:29,786 --> 00:59:31,254
and she asks me for a second date.

1606
00:59:31,321 --> 00:59:32,622
I'm concerned about...

1607
00:59:32,689 --> 00:59:34,224
What if she's genuinely into me?

1608
00:59:34,691 --> 00:59:36,192
I hear there's another meetup.

1609
00:59:36,259 --> 00:59:39,696
What if my attempt at a joke
ruins her mood?

1610
00:59:40,964 --> 00:59:41,965
You'd go that far?

1611
00:59:42,031 --> 00:59:43,066
JUST EAT THE <i>JAPCHAE, </i>DANIEL

1612
00:59:43,266 --> 00:59:44,667
When it comes to asking
for another date

1613
00:59:44,734 --> 00:59:46,035
isn't my best option
keeping it casual?

1614
00:59:46,369 --> 00:59:48,338
I once had a blind date

1615
00:59:49,038 --> 00:59:50,106
and we met in Hongdae.

1616
00:59:50,173 --> 00:59:52,108
My date back then
lived in Sadang-dong.

1617
00:59:52,175 --> 00:59:53,810
He said he'd text me when he got home

1618
00:59:53,877 --> 00:59:54,978
but he never did.

1619
00:59:55,044 --> 00:59:56,512
I guess he hasn't made it home yet.

1620
00:59:57,680 --> 00:59:58,681
Do-yeon.

1621
00:59:58,748 --> 00:59:59,916
Otherwise, he's gay.

1622
01:00:00,650 --> 01:00:01,751
Otherwise, he's gay.

1623
01:00:07,156 --> 01:00:08,691
That's how I find peace of mind.

1624
01:00:08,758 --> 01:00:10,827
- Your ears have turned red again.
- They're beet red.

1625
01:00:10,894 --> 01:00:12,595
That guy must've
really pissed her off.

1626
01:00:12,662 --> 01:00:14,631
- Look, she's turned scarlet.
- The memory ticked her off.

1627
01:00:14,697 --> 01:00:15,832
So he really didn't reach out.

1628
01:00:15,899 --> 01:00:17,300
WE HOPE... YOU'RE DOING WELL

1629
01:00:17,667 --> 01:00:19,302
- We're short on time.
- Let's go get prepared.

1630
01:00:19,369 --> 01:00:21,037
- You're right.
- Go get washed up.

1631
01:00:21,571 --> 01:00:26,409
UPSIDE OF LIVING TOGETHER
GIRL PALS WILL REVIEW YOUR OUTFIT

1632
01:00:27,277 --> 01:00:28,611
Shouldn't we play some music?

1633
01:00:30,280 --> 01:00:33,249
BGM FOR A BOYFRIEND LOOK SHOWCASE

1634
01:00:33,316 --> 01:00:35,018
- What do you think?
- I don't know.

1635
01:00:35,084 --> 01:00:38,221
It sounds like something
you'd hear in a store.

1636
01:00:38,288 --> 01:00:39,289
So I guess...

1637
01:00:39,355 --> 01:00:41,457
SO EXCITED THAT SHE JUMPS TO HER FEET

1638
01:00:42,659 --> 01:00:45,028
STRUTTING DOWN THE CATWALK

1639
01:00:46,229 --> 01:00:48,231
Look, this is how guys walk
all nonchalant.

1640
01:00:48,898 --> 01:00:50,333
NONCHALANT

1641
01:00:50,633 --> 01:00:51,901
ALOOF

1642
01:00:53,303 --> 01:00:54,871
How come you manage to look so cool?

1643
01:00:54,938 --> 01:00:56,172
How do you do it so well?

1644
01:00:56,239 --> 01:00:57,340
"Don't fall for me, okay?"

1645
01:00:57,407 --> 01:00:58,675
HYPED UP JUST AS THE DATE ATTENDEES

1646
01:00:59,075 --> 01:01:00,510
- I can't wait to see them.
- Same.

1647
01:01:01,778 --> 01:01:04,047
But if they dressed up
as much as they could

1648
01:01:04,113 --> 01:01:05,315
