- Oh, my nails...

2180
01:20:58,373 --> 01:20:59,875
Why don't I take this and...

2181
01:20:59,941 --> 01:21:00,942
EMBARRASSED

2182
01:21:01,676 --> 01:21:02,844
I can knead her clay.

2183
01:21:02,911 --> 01:21:04,012
Thank you.

2184
01:21:04,079 --> 01:21:05,847
- He's so sweet.
- I can do it for you.

2185
01:21:06,548 --> 01:21:07,549
Why don't I try it like this?

2186
01:21:07,616 --> 01:21:08,884
My gosh.

2187
01:21:09,618 --> 01:21:10,785
That's a great idea.

2188
01:21:10,852 --> 01:21:12,354
- Do you think it will turn out well?
- Sure.

2189
01:21:13,155 --> 01:21:14,689
I couldn't have thought of that.

2190
01:21:14,756 --> 01:21:15,757
You're doing it my way?

2191
01:21:15,824 --> 01:21:17,159
Of course.

2192
01:21:19,294 --> 01:21:21,763
STUDIES CAREFULLY

2193
01:21:23,098 --> 01:21:24,633
The layers should be even
in thickness.

2194
01:21:24,699 --> 01:21:27,135
You have beautiful hands
with long fingers.

2195
01:21:28,303 --> 01:21:30,005
Your hands are the beautiful ones.

2196
01:21:30,071 --> 01:21:31,306
- Oh, mine?
- Yes.

2197
01:21:31,373 --> 01:21:32,707
Your fingers are lean and long.

2198
01:21:33,241 --> 01:21:34,242
IRKED

2199
01:21:34,309 --> 01:21:37,012
Excuse me, but could you keep it down
and help us all focus?

2200
01:21:37,479 --> 01:21:40,081
- I get you have lovely hands...
- Seriously, you talk too much.

2201
01:21:40,148 --> 01:21:42,717
- We can't hold a conversation here.
- Let's focus on our art pieces.

2202
01:21:42,784 --> 01:21:44,819
We've just begun

2203
01:21:44,886 --> 01:21:46,288
and you're already
in a lovey-dovey mood.

2204
01:21:46,354 --> 01:21:47,789
But we haven't said much.

2205
01:21:48,223 --> 01:21:50,125
It's because you're the sweetest.

2206
01:21:50,625 --> 01:21:52,260
Just like this...

2207
01:21:53,995 --> 01:21:55,397
So this is how you do it.

2208
01:21:56,565 --> 01:21:58,934
WORDLESSLY BEING KIND

2209
01:21:59,634 --> 01:22:01,903
So you graduated
from a Japanese college, right?

2210
01:22:01,970 --> 01:22:03,738
Yes, that's right.

2211
01:22:03,805 --> 01:22:05,974
You would've had
to stay abroad, then.

2212
01:22:06,041 --> 01:22:07,042
That's right.

2213
01:22:07,108 --> 01:22:09,711
But I had it pretty easy.

2214
01:22:09,778 --> 01:22:11,146
- You had an easy time there?
- Yes.

2215
01:22:11,213 --> 01:22:12,781
- Thanks to Keun-suk?
- Right.

2216
01:22:12,847 --> 01:22:14,749
- Did your friends speak Korean?
- That's right.

2217
01:22:14,816 --> 01:22:18,453
Everyone loved his show,
<i>Ikemen Desuyone.</i>

2218
01:22:18,520 --> 01:22:19,854
- Oh, <i>You Are Beautiful?</i>
- Yes.

2219
01:22:19,921 --> 01:22:21,056
Let's keep it down, guys.

2220
01:22:21,690 --> 01:22:22,857
- We're here to...
- Keun-suk.

2221
01:22:22,924 --> 01:22:25,393
Back when Aurora
was studying in Japan

2222
01:22:25,460 --> 01:22:28,563
your work made her life there
a walk in the park.

2223
01:22:28,630 --> 01:22:29,831
- That's right.
- Because your show

2224
01:22:29,898 --> 01:22:31,600
was a common ground
for her and her friends.

2225
01:22:31,666 --> 01:22:33,001
- Really?
- That's right.

2226
01:22:33,835 --> 01:22:37,572
Where does Keun-suk stand
in the Japanese showbiz industry?

2227
01:22:37,839 --> 01:22:39,507
He's literally Asia Prince.

2228
01:22:39,574 --> 01:22:41,910
- He's number one.
- His popularity is no joke.

2229
01:22:41,977 --> 01:22:44,079
- It's just a silly nickname.
- I was blown away.

2230
01:22:44,145 --> 01:22:45,146
It's nothing.

2231
01:22:45,213 --> 01:22:47,782
How did you come to know
that he's Asia Prince?

2232
01:22:47,849 --> 01:22:48,984
He told me all about it.

2233
01:22:50,852 --> 01:22:52,387
He introduced himself as AP
when we first met.

2234
01:22:52,454 --> 01:22:53,888
- Himself?
- Yes.

2235
01:22:53,955 --> 01:22:55,624
So I thought
"So that guy is Asia Prince."

2236
01:22:55,690 --> 01:22:58,226
You guys are making me dizzy.

2237
01:22:58,893 --> 01:23:00,662
After I take
the completed utensil rest home

2238
01:23:01,096 --> 01:23:03,331
I'll think of you
every time I have breakfast.

2239
01:23:05,267 --> 01:23:06,868
EMBARRASSED BY HIS OWN LINE

2240
01:23:06,935 --> 01:23:08,003
Can't I do that?

2241
01:23:10,905 --> 01:23:13,408
BURSTS INTO LAUGHTER, SNICKERS

2242
01:23:13,975 --> 01:23:15,910
DIDN'T HE NAG AT ME FOR CHATTING?

2243
01:23:16,144 --> 01:23:19,381
Why do I get the feeling
you'll have 20 of these at home?

2244
01:23:19,581 --> 01:23:21,283
- Actually, I have 200.
- A whopping 200 of these.

2245
01:23:22,617 --> 01:23:23,885
What's with these guys?

2246
01:23:25,287 --> 01:23:26,488
Let's call it the power of love.

2247
01:23:27,122 --> 01:23:29,124
- How romantic.
- Really?

2248
01:23:29,190 --> 01:23:31,126
- That's your response?
- That's your takeaway?

2249
01:23:31,192 --> 01:23:32,460
That's a stretch, isn't it?

2250
01:23:32,527 --> 01:23:33,795
FLIRTATIOUS QUIPS FLOWING NON-STOP

2251
01:23:34,829 --> 01:23:39,434
What type of person were you
hoping to meet here?

2252
01:23:39,501 --> 01:23:42,837
I just wondered who I'd get to meet
and enjoyed the excitement.

2253
01:23:42,904 --> 01:23:45,340
I wasn't hoping to meet
a specific type here.

2254
01:23:48,276 --> 01:23:50,378
Were you excited?

2255
01:23:50,445 --> 01:23:51,946
Yes, I was.

2256
01:23:52,013 --> 01:23:54,049
I'm having fun,
and I'm far more relaxed now

2257
01:23:54,115 --> 01:23:55,317
compared to earlier.

2258
01:23:55,383 --> 01:23:56,985
- At first, I was kind of nervous.
- Me too.

2259
01:23:58,486 --> 01:24:01,856
Mind if I ask your favorite fruit?

2260
01:24:02,257 --> 01:24:03,992
- Favorite fruit?
- Yes.

2261
01:24:04,693 --> 01:24:05,827
Shine Muscat.

2262
01:24:05,894 --> 01:24:07,562
- Shine Muscat?
- Yes.

2263
01:24:08,697 --> 01:24:10,231
Why did you ask
about my favorite fruit?

2264
01:24:11,700 --> 01:24:14,235
- You just reminded me of fruit.
- I did?

2265
01:24:14,302 --> 01:24:15,904
I got the feeling you'd like it.

2266
01:24:16,171 --> 01:24:17,205
Perhaps something zesty?

2267
01:24:17,272 --> 01:24:21,810
Which fruit do you think
would suit me best?

2268
01:24:23,778 --> 01:24:24,913
Korean melons?

2269
01:24:24,979 --> 01:24:26,481
Korean melons? May I ask why?

2270
01:24:28,550 --> 01:24:32,921
I NEED TO GIVE A WINNING ANSWER...

2271
01:24:32,987 --> 01:24:34,022
You're shaking, aren't you?

2272
01:24:34,089 --> 01:24:35,724
- You know...
- Yes?

2273
01:24:36,291 --> 01:24:38,693
- They have the golden ones.
- Yes.

2274
01:24:38,760 --> 01:24:40,095
You're sweet like golden ones.

2275
01:24:42,297 --> 01:24:44,532
- In a good way.
- Thank you.

2276
01:24:44,599 --> 01:24:45,834
In a very good way.

2277
01:24:45,900 --> 01:24:47,535
I've never been likened
to Korean melons before.

2278
01:24:47,602 --> 01:24:48,903
Really?

2279
01:24:48,970 --> 01:24:50,739
I meant that as a great compliment.

2280
01:24:51,439 --> 01:24:53,274
Oh, I get it. Is this pickled radish?

2281
01:24:53,341 --> 01:24:55,844
- Are you making <i>kimbap?</i>
- No.

2282
01:24:55,910 --> 01:24:57,579
Look, like this.

2283
01:24:58,079 --> 01:24:59,080
What is it, though?

2284
01:24:59,147 --> 01:25:00,281
A tongue?

2285
01:25:01,750 --> 01:25:04,185
Wait, I guess you were trying
to shape it like this.

2286
01:25:04,252 --> 01:25:05,787
Did you need another rolling pin?

2287
01:25:06,855 --> 01:25:07,889
No.

2288
01:25:07,956 --> 01:25:09,691
SOMEHOW, SHE'S LOVING IT

2289
01:25:10,558 --> 01:25:12,894
We're making something truly unique.

2290
01:25:12,961 --> 01:25:16,097
Have you seen something like this
at a shop? I bet you haven't.

2291
01:25:16,164 --> 01:25:17,465
Because folks wouldn't buy it.

2292
01:25:18,700 --> 01:25:19,768
I guess.

2293
01:25:19,834 --> 01:25:21,603
- They wouldn't.
- But it'd give you good memories.

2294
01:25:21,669 --> 01:25:22,737
This would? Sure.

2295
01:25:22,971 --> 01:25:24,906
It's proof that our focus
was on each other

2296
01:25:24,973 --> 01:25:27,108
- rather than the pottery.
- Of course.

2297
01:25:27,175 --> 01:25:28,743
- We're hyper-focused.
- Exactly.

2298
01:25:28,810 --> 01:25:30,078
You can say that again.

2299
01:25:30,645 --> 01:25:31,713
When is your birthday?

2300
01:25:32,046 --> 01:25:33,148
I was born in July.

2301
01:25:34,516 --> 01:25:35,884
How's 0207?

2302
01:25:36,651 --> 01:25:37,986
- I was born in February.
- I like it.

2303
01:25:38,052 --> 01:25:39,120
BRAINSTORMING ENGRAVING IDEAS

2304
01:25:39,621 --> 01:25:41,790
- Are there numbers?
- Are you exchanging numbers?

2305
01:25:41,856 --> 01:25:43,491
What does 0207 mean?

2306
01:25:43,558 --> 01:25:44,559
It's our secret.

2307
01:25:45,560 --> 01:25:46,928
Seriously? What's going on?

2308
01:25:46,995 --> 01:25:48,029
You have a secret already?

2309
01:25:48,096 --> 01:25:49,097
GRINNING SHYLY

2310
01:25:49,931 --> 01:25:50,932
What do you think about a guy

2311
01:25:50,999 --> 01:25:52,734
who breaks a sweat
in a pottery class?

2312
01:25:53,435 --> 01:25:56,004
I'd love to wipe it off you,
but my hands aren't exactly clean.

2313
01:25:58,473 --> 01:25:59,974
You have a knack for this.

2314
01:26:00,041 --> 01:26:01,910
Does it look okay?
I bet my talent startled you.

2315
01:26:02,677 --> 01:26:03,678
SLOWLY, THEY GROW CLOSER

2316
01:26:03,745 --> 01:26:06,314
His work looks like something
you'd find in a store.

2317
01:26:07,215 --> 01:26:09,451
Here's what I love about this event.

2318
01:26:09,651 --> 01:26:11,686
I don't think
I could've been so frank

2319
01:26:11,753 --> 01:26:13,221
while maintaining eye contact.

2320
01:26:13,288 --> 01:26:14,656
- Right.
- It'd be so awkward.

2321
01:26:14,722 --> 01:26:17,992
But we can chat slowly
while focusing on the shared project.

2322
01:26:18,059 --> 01:26:20,628
It's really soothing.

2323
01:26:20,695 --> 01:26:26,034
I enjoyed listening to you guys talk.

2324
01:26:26,234 --> 01:26:27,669
It's like relaxing white noise.

2325
01:26:28,870 --> 01:26:29,904
<i>Great.</i>

2326
01:26:29,971 --> 01:26:31,105
<i>We're done.</i>

2327
01:26:31,573 --> 01:26:33,441
<i>- We're done, too.</i>
<i>- Same here.</i>

2328
01:26:33,508 --> 01:26:34,576
AP, KOALA

2329
01:26:34,642 --> 01:26:38,680
ENGAGING IN A CONVERSATION
WITH A WELCOME STRANGER

2330
01:26:38,746 --> 01:26:41,149
<i>It will be so strange and wonderful</i>
<i>to see the finished work later.</i>

2331
01:26:41,216 --> 01:26:44,052
<i>You're here to get to know</i>
<i>many different people.</i>

2332
01:26:45,053 --> 01:26:47,489
"How many dates a week is ideal?"

2333
01:26:47,555 --> 01:26:49,023
Is that important?

2334
01:26:49,090 --> 01:26:50,792
Don't you think
that's the power of love?

2335
01:26:50,859 --> 01:26:52,060
THEY GROW BOLDER

2336
01:26:53,628 --> 01:26:54,629
You want to hold hands?

2337
01:26:54,696 --> 01:26:57,765
THEIR AMBITIOUS WINNING MOVES
BECOME EQUALLY BOLDER

2338
01:26:57,832 --> 01:26:59,467
What did I do so wrong?

2339
01:26:59,534 --> 01:27:01,936
THE FRANK AND DARING GROUP DATE
WILL CONTINUE IN THE NEXT EPISODE

2340
01:27:03,171 --> 01:27:05,507
A GLAMOROUS EVENING PARTY

2341
01:27:05,573 --> 01:27:09,277
WITH ALL EYES ON HER

2342
01:27:09,344 --> 01:27:10,478
You look beautiful.

2343
01:27:11,613 --> 01:27:12,714
You look different.

2344
01:27:15,850 --> 01:27:19,888
<i>I might've fallen for you</i>
<i>if we had met like this.</i>

2345
01:27:19,954 --> 01:27:22,323
ARE THINGS CHANGING BETWEEN US?

2346
01:27:22,657 --> 01:27:24,592
Will you dance with me?

2347
01:27:26,794 --> 01:27:30,698
DANIEL'S HEART-POUNDING DREAM
HOUSE SQUAD GOAL

2348
01:27:31,099 --> 01:27:32,367
<i>We're the main characters.</i>

2349
01:27:34,302 --> 01:27:36,971
<i>- You two look great together.</i>
<i>- Don't they look great together?</i>

2350
01:27:38,973 --> 01:27:40,975
Subtitles by Jeongwoo Kim
